WEBVTT

00:02.958 --> 00:05.541
[female reporter]
Shadyside, small-town America.

00:06.541 --> 00:10.833
But among locals, a history of horror
has earned it another nickname,

00:11.500 --> 00:13.291
"Killer Capital USA."

00:14.541 --> 00:15.375
And last night…

00:15.458 --> 00:17.375
[tires screeching]

00:18.750 --> 00:20.250
…tragedy struck again.

00:21.833 --> 00:23.875
I'm here with Sheriff Nick Goode.

00:23.958 --> 00:26.708
Sheriff, what can you tell us?

00:26.791 --> 00:28.375
Um, there were seven victims.

00:29.166 --> 00:32.291
-[screams]
-[Josh] None of this… is random.

00:32.375 --> 00:33.875
[Deena] Oh my God!

00:33.958 --> 00:36.000
[Josh] These massacres
are connected to Sarah Fier.

00:37.041 --> 00:39.708
[Josh] 1666,
Sarah Fier was hanged for witchcraft.

00:41.666 --> 00:44.208
She's been possessing people,
turning them into killers,

00:44.291 --> 00:45.916
to take revenge on the town.

00:46.000 --> 00:47.333
[gunshots]

00:47.875 --> 00:48.833
[tires screeching]

00:49.875 --> 00:50.750
[Kate] Go! Go!

00:50.833 --> 00:53.583
[menacing music crescendos]

00:54.291 --> 00:57.125
But in 1978,
there was one survivor, C. Berman.

00:57.208 --> 00:58.333
She's the key.

01:06.416 --> 01:07.458
[Deena] It's over.

01:08.875 --> 01:09.875
[C. Berman] Over?

01:10.375 --> 01:11.500
It's never over.

01:11.583 --> 01:13.291
[whispering voice echoes] Sam…

01:17.416 --> 01:19.416
[Deena grunting, screaming]

01:19.500 --> 01:21.083
[Sam grunting]

01:22.250 --> 01:23.750
[Deena] Get off!

01:26.583 --> 01:28.833
-[grunting]
-[fly buzzing]

01:30.041 --> 01:32.166
-I'm going to get you back.
-[roars]

01:42.666 --> 01:45.166
[eerie music playing]

01:52.833 --> 01:54.916
[female reporter] Killer Capital, USA.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.541
After a week of terror,

01:56.625 --> 01:59.916
Shadyside continues to live up
to its twisted nickname.

02:00.000 --> 02:01.875
Clad in a Halloween skull mask,

02:01.958 --> 02:04.208
Shadyside High graduate Ryan Torres

02:04.291 --> 02:07.416
kicked off the days of terror
with a massacre at the mall.

02:07.500 --> 02:11.291
And now an already mourning community
is plunged into horror yet again

02:11.375 --> 02:15.083
as the Sheriff's Department reports
more carnage at East Union Medical.

02:15.166 --> 02:18.291
Police believe the murders
were fueled by amphetamines.

02:18.375 --> 02:21.791
Local teenagers Kate Schmidt
and Simon Kalivoda

02:21.875 --> 02:23.666
are the primary suspects.

02:23.750 --> 02:27.250
The scene of the final carnage
was the local grocery store.

02:27.333 --> 02:32.250
Sheriff Nick Goode found the Grab and Bag
soaked in blood and broken dreams.

02:33.250 --> 02:35.958
[alarm bell ringing]

02:42.958 --> 02:44.333
[clocks ticking]

02:46.041 --> 02:47.083
[sighs]

02:47.166 --> 02:49.291
["The Man Who Sold The World" playing]

02:59.166 --> 03:01.958
-♪ We passed upon the stair… ♪
-[alarm clock buzzing]

03:02.958 --> 03:06.708
-[dog barking]
-♪ We spoke of was and when ♪

03:07.750 --> 03:10.875
♪ Although I wasn't there… ♪

03:10.958 --> 03:12.375
[dog barking]

03:12.458 --> 03:14.791
♪ He said I was his friend… ♪

03:14.875 --> 03:16.250
[dog barking]

03:17.041 --> 03:18.250
Major, Jesus!

03:18.333 --> 03:20.375
[Major barking]

03:20.458 --> 03:22.166
-[alarm bell ringing]
-[groans]

03:22.250 --> 03:23.583
God damn it!

03:23.666 --> 03:26.500
-[music fades out]
-[menacing music playing]

03:26.583 --> 03:27.583
[alarm bell ringing]

03:27.666 --> 03:29.458
[Major barking]

03:31.791 --> 03:34.166
You're an impatient bastard, aren't you?

03:38.041 --> 03:39.833
[man on TV] Sunnyvale is a city of hope.

03:40.416 --> 03:44.125
My family have lived here for generations,
cultivating the growth of our city.

03:44.708 --> 03:46.583
And now, as I take the torch

03:47.208 --> 03:49.541
-carried by my forefathers…
-[rapid knocking on door]

03:49.625 --> 03:52.750
…I'm ready to bring my experience
to City Hall for another two years.

03:53.291 --> 03:55.625
-[knocking continues]
-I understand the challenges…

03:55.708 --> 03:57.750
[door handle rattling]

03:57.833 --> 04:01.125
[indistinct talk on TV]

04:01.208 --> 04:02.583
[Will Goode] I'm here to listen.

04:03.083 --> 04:06.833
Let's work together
to keep Sunnyvale shining!

04:10.375 --> 04:12.500
[ominous music playing]

04:13.583 --> 04:16.791
[whispering] It's OK. You stay here.
I'm gonna keep us safe, OK?

04:16.875 --> 04:19.291
[Major whimpering]

04:27.875 --> 04:30.375
-[window rattling]
-[breathing heavily]

04:39.791 --> 04:40.833
[woman grunts]

04:40.916 --> 04:43.500
-Don't fucking move!
-[Deena] Wait, wait!

04:43.583 --> 04:46.458
Stop, please! Please! We called you.

04:46.541 --> 04:49.750
Hello, my name is Deena Johnson.
We need to know how you survived!

04:49.833 --> 04:52.541
Hey! We're being attacked, alright?
There are killers here!

04:52.625 --> 04:55.458
-[Deena] Pick up! We need your help!
-[Josh] Please!

04:55.541 --> 04:57.416
[telephone ringing]

04:58.125 --> 04:59.958
-Hello?
-You're still alive.

05:01.375 --> 05:02.708
C. Berman…

05:02.791 --> 05:03.791
[gasps]

05:05.416 --> 05:06.916
Why the hell would you come here?

05:11.583 --> 05:12.916
-[grunting]
-[C. Berman] No!

05:13.000 --> 05:17.125
No, no, no! You need to leave! Right now!
You have no idea what you are doing!

05:17.208 --> 05:19.458
[Deena] Wait! Yeah, exactly.

05:19.541 --> 05:22.500
You are the only person
who knows what we're dealing with.

05:22.583 --> 05:26.458
I don't want that thing near me.
Get that car and "it" off my property.

05:26.541 --> 05:27.833
Her name is Sam.

05:27.916 --> 05:30.750
You could have watched us dead
on the six o'clock news,

05:30.833 --> 05:31.916
but you didn't.

05:32.541 --> 05:33.875
You called us back.

05:33.958 --> 05:36.541
[sighs] I can't help you with this!

05:36.625 --> 05:39.041
You are our last chance! The witch--

05:39.125 --> 05:40.291
No, I'm sorry.

05:40.375 --> 05:44.333
[Deena] My girlfriend is possessed by her
and tied up in a trunk, but you…

05:45.125 --> 05:46.666
you saw her and you survived.

05:46.750 --> 05:49.333
What was different? Please.

05:49.416 --> 05:53.208
Maybe something happened to you,
something that can help us stop her.

05:53.291 --> 05:55.666
[C. Berman] There's not!
You can't stop her.

05:55.750 --> 05:59.208
Run, far as you can, fast as you can!

05:59.291 --> 06:00.875
That is your only chance.

06:00.958 --> 06:03.458
Look, I can't just run!

06:04.125 --> 06:05.333
Look, Sam…

06:06.666 --> 06:08.000
I can't let her die.

06:09.333 --> 06:10.333
I won't!

06:12.250 --> 06:13.333
I love her.

06:15.500 --> 06:16.583
Please!

06:21.041 --> 06:23.625
Just keep her away from Major Tom.

06:27.750 --> 06:29.833
[Sam grunting]

06:31.625 --> 06:34.375
[Sam grunting]

06:38.000 --> 06:39.833
[Sam grunting]

06:40.750 --> 06:41.833
[Deena clears throat]

06:45.583 --> 06:46.833
It's completely fine.

06:47.750 --> 06:50.166
She's tied up in the bathroom,
so she, like,

06:50.250 --> 06:52.458
totally can't leave now, we're cool.

06:52.541 --> 06:54.000
[Sam roars]

06:54.083 --> 06:55.208
[Josh] Yep, cool.

06:55.708 --> 06:56.750
Cool, cool.

07:01.458 --> 07:02.458
Take a seat.

07:03.916 --> 07:06.041
[clocks ticking]

07:09.375 --> 07:10.750
[C. Berman] In Shadyside,

07:10.833 --> 07:12.625
the past is never really past.

07:12.708 --> 07:14.166
[breathes shakily]

07:17.458 --> 07:21.291
-This was July… 12th.
-[clocks ticking]

07:21.875 --> 07:24.166
[C. Berman] The summer of 1978.

07:24.666 --> 07:26.333
The first day of camp.

07:28.375 --> 07:29.708
[inhales deeply]

07:33.541 --> 07:35.875
A week later, my sister was dead.

07:37.625 --> 07:40.583
-[ominous music playing]
-[clock chiming]

07:46.916 --> 07:48.833
[girl screams]

07:50.458 --> 07:52.875
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit, shit, shit!

07:52.958 --> 07:54.291
[panting]

07:57.708 --> 08:00.166
[dramatic music playing]

08:04.250 --> 08:05.208
[she grunts]

08:06.083 --> 08:08.083
[coughing, gasps]

08:08.875 --> 08:10.166
[ravens cawing]

08:10.250 --> 08:12.416
[gasping, groans]

08:14.666 --> 08:16.416
You're gonna hang, witch.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.958
[kids chanting]
Before the witch's final breath,

08:19.041 --> 08:20.791
she found a way to cheat her death.

08:20.875 --> 08:21.875
[redhead] Oh God!

08:21.958 --> 08:24.916
[chanting] By cutting off her wicked hand,
she kept her grip upon our land!

08:25.000 --> 08:28.708
She reaches from beyond the grave,
to make good men her evil slaves.

08:28.791 --> 08:32.666
She'll take your blood, take your head,
she'll follow you until you're dead.

08:32.750 --> 08:35.083
-[redhead grunts]
-[girl 1] String her up.

08:35.916 --> 08:37.916
[redhead] No, stop it! Stop it! Stop.

08:38.000 --> 08:39.625
[gasps]

08:39.708 --> 08:41.666
Let me down, you shits! Let me down!

08:47.333 --> 08:50.750
-Well, well. What do we have here?
-Goddamn thief!

08:50.833 --> 08:52.875
[girl 1] No. No, she's no thief.

08:53.458 --> 08:55.708
She's possessed by the witch.

08:55.791 --> 08:58.083
The only way to explain
her psycho behavior.

08:58.166 --> 08:59.833
-Fuck you!
-[they gasp]

08:59.916 --> 09:02.291
[redhead panting]

09:02.375 --> 09:03.750
Guess we're even now.

09:04.541 --> 09:06.875
You do know what they did
to Sarah Fier, right?

09:07.625 --> 09:08.791
They hanged her,

09:09.791 --> 09:10.833
from this very tree.

09:11.500 --> 09:14.583
But she'd have died forever if you did
what you always do to witches…

09:15.458 --> 09:16.541
You burn them.

09:18.416 --> 09:20.500
-Give me your lighter!
-What?

09:20.583 --> 09:21.791
Give it to me!

09:23.291 --> 09:24.416
Now, hold her legs.

09:24.500 --> 09:25.416
Seriously, Sheila?

09:25.500 --> 09:27.416
Do it! [flicks lighter open]

09:27.500 --> 09:31.083
No, no, no! Stop it!
Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

09:31.166 --> 09:34.000
-Shut up, you witch.
-Sheila! You made your point.

09:34.083 --> 09:36.666
-Don't! Don't!
-[boy] Sheila, it was only ten bucks.

09:38.083 --> 09:39.750
[girl 2] Are we really gonna do this?

09:40.500 --> 09:41.583
-Sheila!
-No, no, no!

09:41.666 --> 09:43.875
-[girl 2] Sheila!
-[screams]

09:43.958 --> 09:46.791
-[Sheila] Shit! Will, your brother.
-The hell is this? Let her down!

09:46.875 --> 09:48.041
Nick, I can explain.

09:48.125 --> 09:51.000
Let her down, Will!
I swear to God I'll tell Mom!

09:52.208 --> 09:53.708
[grunts]

09:53.791 --> 09:56.375
[Sheila] I went back to my cabin,
the door was open.

09:56.458 --> 09:59.833
All my money was gone
and Ziggy was just sprinting away.

09:59.916 --> 10:03.750
-Because you were chasing me.
-Ziggy! You talk when I tell you to talk.

10:05.041 --> 10:07.291
-Did you see her take it?
-Everyone did.

10:07.375 --> 10:08.833
-[girls] Everyone.
-Alright.

10:09.750 --> 10:12.583
Well, that's it, Berman.
Five strikes. You're out.

10:12.666 --> 10:16.458
-I'm out? They just tried to murder me!
-Yeah. And I'll deal with them.

10:16.541 --> 10:20.625
But first, get back to camp, call Mommy
because you're done at Nightwing.

10:21.125 --> 10:23.250
-I didn't do it.
-[boy 2] Oh, yeah?

10:23.333 --> 10:25.208
Like you didn't set the camp flag on fire?

10:25.291 --> 10:28.916
Or let out the camp rabbits?
Or graffiti the outhouse stalls?

10:29.416 --> 10:31.041
-I warned you--
-[Sheila] Kurt.

10:31.125 --> 10:33.000
It's not her fault, really.

10:35.041 --> 10:37.791
-She's possessed by Sarah Fier.
-Oh, you…

10:38.416 --> 10:40.916
-[Kurt] Hey, hey, hey!
-[Nick] Hey, hey.

10:42.250 --> 10:45.125
We kick her out, somebody's gonna ask
about the burn on her arm.

10:45.208 --> 10:47.000
Then who's in trouble? Huh?

10:47.083 --> 10:49.583
Why don't we just let this one slide?
Yeah?

10:51.291 --> 10:55.666
Alright. One more strike and you're out
for real. You hear me, Berman?

10:55.750 --> 10:56.833
One more.

10:58.375 --> 11:00.208
Being bossed around by a Goode.

11:00.750 --> 11:03.416
Wow, some things never change.

11:07.541 --> 11:09.458
God, I hate that little bitch.

11:10.541 --> 11:11.958
[children playing, shouting]

11:12.041 --> 11:13.041
[Nick] Hey.

11:14.958 --> 11:18.708
-Have Nurse Lane check that burn out.
-I'm gonna let it get infected and die.

11:18.791 --> 11:20.291
[Nick] I don't get a thank you?

11:20.375 --> 11:21.375
[Ziggy] Oh!

11:22.083 --> 11:23.541
I'm sorry, I forgot!

11:24.291 --> 11:26.041
Thank you, King of Sunnyvale,

11:26.125 --> 11:28.000
future Police Chief Nick Goode,

11:28.083 --> 11:31.625
for rescuing poor, helpless Shadysider me!

11:31.708 --> 11:33.375
How could I ever repay you?

11:33.458 --> 11:37.166
Oh, I know. I'll bat my eyes at you,
like all the other dumbass girls.

11:38.166 --> 11:42.708
["Brother Love's Traveling Salvation Show"
playing]

11:45.750 --> 11:49.083
♪ Hot August night ♪

11:49.166 --> 11:54.208
♪ And the leaves hanging down
The grass on the ground smelling sweet ♪

11:56.791 --> 11:59.583
♪ Move up the road… ♪

12:00.250 --> 12:01.500
-Boo!
-[girls scream]

12:01.583 --> 12:04.708
♪ And the sound of that good gospel beat ♪

12:08.375 --> 12:10.458
♪ Sits a ragged tent ♪

12:12.000 --> 12:14.000
♪ Where there ain't no trees… ♪

12:14.083 --> 12:18.458
Color War begins tonight, guys! Line up
and grab a shirt! Do you have a shirt?

12:18.541 --> 12:21.250
Blue is for beautiful,
if you live in Shadyside.

12:21.333 --> 12:23.875
Red is for radiance,
if you live in Sunnyvale.

12:23.958 --> 12:26.958
Despite our differences,
we're all perfect!

12:28.041 --> 12:29.791
Even you, Ziggy Berman!

12:29.875 --> 12:31.375
♪ And grab the old ladies ♪

12:31.458 --> 12:33.625
♪ And everyone goes ♪

12:33.708 --> 12:36.375
♪ 'Cause everyone knows… ♪ [fades out]

12:36.458 --> 12:39.750
["Love Will Keep Us Together"
playing over stereo]

12:39.833 --> 12:42.375
♪ Stop, I'll be thinking of you… ♪

12:42.458 --> 12:44.875
[girl grunting] What is this gunk?

12:44.958 --> 12:47.708
It just… It won't come off!

12:48.291 --> 12:50.833
That's been there forever, babe.
Just give that up.

12:50.916 --> 12:52.958
-Tommy!
-I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

12:53.041 --> 12:56.416
You're right.
It's just, you know, Color War is tonight.

12:56.500 --> 12:57.958
I'm well aware!

12:58.041 --> 13:00.041
We also have to get the Mess Hall ready.

13:00.541 --> 13:01.750
[girl] Oh my gosh.

13:02.333 --> 13:05.833
Oh my gosh. This gosh darn moss!

13:05.916 --> 13:07.708
It's… it's all over me!

13:07.791 --> 13:11.375
Oh, hey! It's OK! This isn't a big deal.

13:11.458 --> 13:14.375
What? No, it's not OK!
It… it… it's stained!

13:14.958 --> 13:18.625
Only Cindy Berman would expect
to clean the outhouse and not get dirty.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.666
It's not funny!

13:21.666 --> 13:22.791
It's kinda funny.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.791
♪ While others pretend ♪

13:25.875 --> 13:29.125
♪ I need you now and I need you then ♪

13:29.208 --> 13:30.500
♪ Just stop… ♪

13:31.458 --> 13:32.958
[Cindy gasps] Hey!

13:34.083 --> 13:37.333
-What did we talk about?
-[laughing] I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

13:38.333 --> 13:39.416
You better be.

13:39.916 --> 13:43.000
♪ Keep us together ♪

13:43.708 --> 13:44.875
♪ Whatever ♪

13:44.958 --> 13:46.875
-[stereo clicks]
-[music stops]

13:47.458 --> 13:48.458
What is it?

13:53.250 --> 13:55.500
[breathing heavily]

13:55.583 --> 13:57.291
Where are they?

13:57.375 --> 13:58.791
["Cherry Bomb" playing]

13:58.875 --> 14:01.458
[moaning]

14:02.458 --> 14:04.000
[woman groaning] Harder!

14:04.083 --> 14:05.458
[both groaning]

14:06.041 --> 14:07.375
[woman] Oh my God!

14:08.000 --> 14:09.500
Oh my… Oh my God!

14:09.583 --> 14:11.125
[panting]

14:11.208 --> 14:12.125
Hey.

14:12.208 --> 14:14.875
-Um… what are you doing?
-Three guesses.

14:14.958 --> 14:16.208
[man] Hey, careful.

14:16.291 --> 14:18.666
-You don't wanna corrupt her virgin ears.
-[she laughs]

14:18.750 --> 14:22.125
[Cindy] We have to get everything together
for Color War. And you guys…

14:22.208 --> 14:24.791
uh, uh… have to finish cleaning
the outhouse.

14:24.875 --> 14:29.416
We're doing the shit jobs all summer,
now we have to clean up actual shit? No.

14:29.500 --> 14:32.375
-I'm sorry, but we don't have a choice.
-[man] Shit.

14:34.125 --> 14:35.708
This is our last one, babe.

14:35.791 --> 14:37.000
[man flicks lighter]

14:39.166 --> 14:40.416
What are you doing?

14:41.083 --> 14:42.375
Three guesses.

14:42.458 --> 14:43.375
[laughs]

14:44.625 --> 14:46.583
-[Cindy groans]
-[music stops]

14:46.666 --> 14:48.916
This isn't funny. We have a job to do.

14:50.375 --> 14:52.291
-Alice, put that down.
-[Alice] Or what?

14:52.375 --> 14:54.208
What, are you gonna snitch on me again?

14:54.291 --> 14:59.500
[chuckles] OK. What if you go talk
to your little friend Nurse Lane.

14:59.583 --> 15:02.500
-About getting us some yellow jackets.
-Yes.

15:02.583 --> 15:04.583
-Or some red birds.
-Both.

15:04.666 --> 15:07.708
And then we'll scrub
all the shit you want.

15:07.791 --> 15:11.583
-Yellow jackets, red… What?
-Drugs, baby. Drugs.

15:11.666 --> 15:13.083
-Just hook us up.
-[Cindy] No!

15:13.958 --> 15:16.208
-No, I won't do that!
-[Alice sighs]

15:16.291 --> 15:18.708
Some people want to do things
with their lives.

15:18.791 --> 15:22.416
So stop screwing with mine
and just do your jobs, please!

15:22.500 --> 15:24.625
Maybe you should have thought about that

15:24.708 --> 15:27.958
before blasting Captain and Tennille
for two hours straight.

15:30.041 --> 15:31.250
Snitch.

15:31.333 --> 15:33.500
[gurgling]

15:33.583 --> 15:35.583
[Alice laughs]

15:36.458 --> 15:38.541
["Cherry Bomb" continues over stereo]

15:38.625 --> 15:39.625
Bye!

15:43.916 --> 15:45.250
-[Kurt] Hey!
-[Cindy gasps]

15:45.333 --> 15:47.708
Where have you been?
I've been looking all over.

15:47.791 --> 15:48.833
Your sister…

15:50.208 --> 15:51.208
[sniffing]

15:51.958 --> 15:53.208
[sniffing]

15:53.291 --> 15:55.500
Cindy Berman, that smell better be skunk.

15:56.666 --> 15:58.000
What about my sister?

15:58.500 --> 16:00.125
[bell ringing]

16:00.208 --> 16:02.333
Nurse Lane! Hello!

16:03.541 --> 16:05.291
I'm in trouble again. Help.

16:06.875 --> 16:09.375
Nurse Lane, come on!
I could die any minute now.

16:11.541 --> 16:14.791
[mysterious music playing]

16:15.458 --> 16:16.458
Nurse Lane?

16:18.041 --> 16:19.041
Nurse Lane?

16:20.958 --> 16:24.041
[mysterious music playing]

16:39.916 --> 16:41.916
-[woman] What are you doing?
-Oh my God!

16:42.000 --> 16:44.958
Nurse Lane, you scared the shit out of me.
[inhales deeply]

16:47.916 --> 16:48.916
Are you OK?

16:49.625 --> 16:50.958
[sighs, sniffs]

16:51.041 --> 16:53.416
I am. Oh my goodness.

16:55.083 --> 16:56.458
Ziggy, Ziggy, Ziggy.

16:57.166 --> 16:58.333
What did we do now?

16:59.166 --> 17:04.333
OK, so you are gonna apply this
once a day for three days. OK?

17:04.416 --> 17:06.500
It's gonna protect against infection.

17:08.375 --> 17:09.500
It's gross.

17:09.583 --> 17:11.750
[scoffs] You'll survive.

17:15.125 --> 17:18.208
So, um… what's the Witch's Mark?

17:19.250 --> 17:23.375
[ominous music playing]

17:24.291 --> 17:27.250
You know about my daughter, right?
Ruby Lane?

17:27.333 --> 17:28.458
Uh…

17:29.208 --> 17:30.875
-I don't--
-Of course you do.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.583
Everybody talks, I know.

17:35.375 --> 17:36.916
Tell me, what do they say?

17:37.916 --> 17:39.833
Uh, um… They say she, uh…

17:40.875 --> 17:42.000
she killed people…

17:43.000 --> 17:44.000
at a party.

17:44.583 --> 17:46.583
-Seven, seven friends.
-Eight.

17:48.625 --> 17:51.000
She killed herself that night too.

17:51.083 --> 17:52.333
So eight.

17:54.541 --> 17:56.250
Ruby was such a sweet girl.

17:58.125 --> 18:00.916
Oh, and she had a sweet voice.
She was in choir.

18:01.000 --> 18:02.666
She wanted to be a singer.

18:02.750 --> 18:06.750
[Ruby singing]
♪ You always hurt the one you love ♪

18:06.833 --> 18:08.500
I was so proud of her.

18:08.583 --> 18:09.750
So proud.

18:11.583 --> 18:14.291
The doctors say
it was a psychotic episode,

18:14.375 --> 18:16.250
that she just snapped.

18:16.333 --> 18:17.750
But the kids…

18:17.833 --> 18:20.166
the kids say Sarah Fier made her do it.

18:20.250 --> 18:22.125
That's a little tight.

18:22.208 --> 18:23.541
-What do you think?
-I don't--

18:23.625 --> 18:26.583
'Cause I think you don't go
from being a sweet girl with dreams

18:26.666 --> 18:29.333
to ripping someone's insides out
with a switchblade.

18:29.416 --> 18:32.291
-Nurse Lane!
-People usually kill for a reason,

18:32.375 --> 18:34.416
and sometimes that reason is justified.

18:34.500 --> 18:36.375
Sometimes killing isn't murder.

18:36.458 --> 18:38.875
-Sometimes it's necessary.
-That's hurting me.

18:38.958 --> 18:40.750
-Sometimes it is good.
-Nurse Lane!

18:46.125 --> 18:48.041
Once a day for three days, OK?

18:48.125 --> 18:50.083
-[bell ringing]
-[door closes]

18:51.250 --> 18:52.416
Hi, Nurse Lane.

18:53.458 --> 18:54.541
Hi, Cindy.

18:55.125 --> 18:56.000
Ziggy.

18:57.250 --> 18:59.875
You realize what happens
if you get kicked out, right?

18:59.958 --> 19:03.625
-How awful that would be for me?
-Did someone do something to Nurse Lane?

19:03.708 --> 19:05.541
Like make fun of her daughter?

19:05.625 --> 19:08.208
-Ziggy, are you listening to me?
-She was upset.

19:08.291 --> 19:09.458
I don't care! I…

19:10.375 --> 19:13.000
-Do you hear what I'm saying to you?
-Loud and clear, ma'am.

19:13.083 --> 19:17.125
You don't, we had this conversation
last week and the week before that.

19:17.208 --> 19:20.083
-I'm not gonna get kicked out.
-That's not what Kurt thinks.

19:20.166 --> 19:22.791
-Yeah, well, Kurt can suck it.
-No! Ziggy, no!

19:22.875 --> 19:24.750
If you get kicked out, I do too.

19:25.500 --> 19:29.750
Mom can't work and take care of you.
Then how will I pay for college, huh?

19:29.833 --> 19:31.833
-[Ziggy scoffs]
-Oh, that's funny to you?

19:32.416 --> 19:33.708
Yeah, kinda.

19:34.625 --> 19:36.708
[chuckles] Explain to me what's so funny.

19:36.791 --> 19:37.916
How dumb you are?

19:38.416 --> 19:41.000
No one gets out of this town,
not even Miss Perfect.

19:41.083 --> 19:43.041
Bet on your way out
you get run over by a bus.

19:43.625 --> 19:48.083
Once in your life,
could you just not be so… so mean?

19:48.166 --> 19:50.416
Could once in your life
you just stop pretending?

19:51.791 --> 19:54.375
You're Shadyside, in case you forgot.

19:55.166 --> 19:56.791
["Bitterblue" playing]

19:56.875 --> 20:00.333
[Cindy] I swear to God
everyone just wants to ruin my life.

20:01.291 --> 20:03.833
Alice just, like…
She just won't let it go.

20:03.916 --> 20:07.458
It's like we're still 12 years old
and her whole goal in life is to…

20:07.541 --> 20:09.958
to punish me for something
that wasn't even my fault.

20:10.041 --> 20:12.000
I can't believe
you guys used to be friends.

20:12.083 --> 20:13.541
And Ziggy… [groans]

20:14.041 --> 20:17.375
It's only a matter of time
before she ends up in jail or worse.

20:17.458 --> 20:20.416
I'm trying to be a good role model
and make something of myself.

20:20.500 --> 20:23.041
But no, no,
I'm the stuck-up priss who hates fun,

20:23.125 --> 20:25.708
which isn't even true at all.
I like fun. I like fun!

20:25.791 --> 20:29.666
I just… I just want
to get out of Shadyside. Is that so crazy?

20:29.750 --> 20:32.000
[gasps] Shit!

20:33.000 --> 20:34.250
Shit!

20:34.333 --> 20:36.166
[laughs] Did Cindy Berman just swear?

20:36.250 --> 20:38.708
Not now, Tommy! Not in the mood!

20:39.833 --> 20:41.041
[Cindy sighs]

20:43.666 --> 20:45.041
[sighs] It's OK.

20:46.041 --> 20:47.791
You're OK. You're OK.

20:47.875 --> 20:49.125
Just… [inhales deeply]

20:49.208 --> 20:50.083
…breathe.

20:50.166 --> 20:52.375
[inhales deeply, sighs]

20:59.250 --> 21:00.333
[gasps]

21:00.416 --> 21:03.083
[suspenseful music playing]

21:03.166 --> 21:04.500
Tommy, is that you?

21:12.791 --> 21:13.791
Tommy?

21:14.875 --> 21:16.875
[ominous music playing]

21:26.083 --> 21:27.375
[breathing heavily]

21:28.708 --> 21:32.208
["The First Cut Is The Deepest" playing]

21:32.291 --> 21:34.958
Tommy, what are you doing? You're really…

21:35.041 --> 21:36.583
♪ …all of my heart… ♪

21:38.833 --> 21:40.041
…freaking me out.

21:41.000 --> 21:42.625
-What is it, babe?
-[Cindy gasps]

21:43.416 --> 21:44.875
[relieved sigh]

21:45.708 --> 21:47.000
[gasps]

21:48.166 --> 21:49.750
-Nurse Lane?
-[Nurse Lane] I'm sorry.

21:49.833 --> 21:50.833
[swallows]

21:51.916 --> 21:53.666
But I can't save you.

21:53.750 --> 21:56.000
[suspenseful music playing]

21:56.083 --> 21:57.625
[Nurse Lane] I saw your name.

21:57.708 --> 21:59.041
I saw it on the wall.

21:59.541 --> 22:00.541
One way or another,

22:01.208 --> 22:02.500
you're gonna die tonight.

22:03.750 --> 22:05.083
What are you talking about?

22:05.583 --> 22:08.833
-[Nurse Lane screams]
-[Tommy grunts]

22:09.666 --> 22:10.666
[Nurse Lane grunts]

22:11.250 --> 22:12.708
[Cindy gasps]

22:14.458 --> 22:15.750
[Nurse Lane grunts]

22:18.666 --> 22:21.375
♪ …to being lucky, she's cursed ♪

22:21.458 --> 22:23.333
♪ That's how I know ♪

22:23.416 --> 22:26.500
♪ The first cut is the deepest ♪

22:26.583 --> 22:28.375
♪ Baby, I know ♪

22:28.458 --> 22:32.666
-♪ The first cut is the deepest ♪
-[gasping]

22:34.833 --> 22:38.791
[police officer] You got history with her?
She had a grudge against you?

22:38.875 --> 22:41.291
No grudge. No, we barely ever talked.

22:41.375 --> 22:44.166
I… I go to get bug spray from her.
That's it.

22:44.250 --> 22:46.375
It just doesn't…
it doesn't make any sense.

22:46.875 --> 22:49.250
Why… why would she do something like this?

22:49.916 --> 22:53.375
-She was nuts, just like her kid.
-Nurse Lane, she never seemed crazy.

22:53.458 --> 22:57.208
That's what she said about her kid, but
sane people don't chop up their friends.

22:57.791 --> 22:59.416
Now, tell me again what happened.

22:59.500 --> 23:02.583
[Tommy] Um… uh…
she… she came into the kitchen…

23:03.750 --> 23:05.708
Hey, witch. So sorry.

23:06.333 --> 23:08.500
I know you and Nurse Psycho were close.

23:09.083 --> 23:11.500
-You can visit her in jail now.
-Fuck off, Sheila.

23:12.791 --> 23:13.958
By the way,

23:14.041 --> 23:16.000
you might want to check your stuff.

23:16.583 --> 23:18.958
I think there was an accident
in cabin five.

23:19.541 --> 23:22.833
[dramatic music playing]

23:22.916 --> 23:25.333
-[girl] Look at her!
-[Sheila] Hurry, witch! Run!

23:26.500 --> 23:27.500
[man 1] Hey, Nicky.

23:28.083 --> 23:29.333
Officer Kapinski.

23:30.375 --> 23:33.708
Been meaning to say I'm sorry
about your Pops. He was a good man.

23:34.583 --> 23:36.833
He was a great man. Taken too soon.

23:36.916 --> 23:39.541
Thank you. Yeah. We all miss him.
Big boots to fill.

23:39.625 --> 23:40.458
[chuckles]

23:40.541 --> 23:44.041
Well, he was at peace, knowing one day
you'd be following in his footsteps.

23:44.125 --> 23:46.125
Sheriff Nick Goode's got
a good ring to it.

23:46.208 --> 23:49.083
You just go easy on me
when you're my boss, huh?

23:50.333 --> 23:53.500
[suspenseful music playing]

23:53.583 --> 23:57.833
[sirens wailing]

24:00.458 --> 24:01.625
[Nurse Lane] I'm sorry.

24:01.708 --> 24:03.041
But I can't save you.

24:04.833 --> 24:08.208
One way or another,
you're gonna die tonight.

24:09.416 --> 24:12.708
-[bell ringing]
-[Kurt] Hey, guys! Dinner time!

24:13.625 --> 24:15.541
[man 2] Hey! Hey, come on!

24:15.625 --> 24:19.208
["The Reaper (Don't Fear)" playing]

24:19.291 --> 24:22.583
-Nurse Lane's daughter killed 7 people.
-[boy] Her daughter was Ruby Lane.

24:22.666 --> 24:26.500
She was clearly possessed…
just like her crazy daughter.

24:26.583 --> 24:28.125
Sarah Fier strikes again.

24:28.208 --> 24:30.708
-[girl] How does the witch choose them?
-[sighs] It's crazy.

24:31.208 --> 24:33.625
-Is Color War gonna be canceled?
-It starts tonight.

24:33.708 --> 24:36.958
Psycho Shadysiders
always fucking ruin everything!

24:37.041 --> 24:40.000
She said one way or another,
I was gonna die tonight.

24:40.583 --> 24:42.166
Spooky!

24:42.250 --> 24:45.958
The kiddos are right.
That's, like, totally witchy behavior.

24:46.041 --> 24:50.166
It's just, there must be some explanation.
The witch isn't real.

24:50.250 --> 24:52.291
-Like what?
-Well, maybe…

24:55.333 --> 24:56.583
Maybe she was on something.

24:56.666 --> 24:59.916
[scoffs] Drugs are peaceful, not violent.

25:00.000 --> 25:02.791
I'm not talking about marijuana.

25:02.875 --> 25:07.750
Just admit you're jealous that the witch
wanted your hubby all to herself!

25:07.833 --> 25:11.375
Be serious, man. Why would Nurse Mary
wanna do something like that?

25:11.458 --> 25:14.500
-Why would she want me dead?
-Oh, no. She wouldn't.

25:15.083 --> 25:16.625
[both] But the witch might!

25:16.708 --> 25:18.208
[girl laughing]

25:18.291 --> 25:20.708
Hey, they're just playing around.

25:21.500 --> 25:23.000
This was nothing, I promise.

25:23.083 --> 25:24.416
Did you see her eyes?

25:25.375 --> 25:28.083
There was something in there,
something wrong.

25:30.583 --> 25:33.500
-[loud clapping]
-[shouting] Alright!

25:34.000 --> 25:36.166
-[cheering]
-Chicks, dicks, listen up!

25:36.250 --> 25:39.708
We had a scary situation earlier,
but we cannot let that mess

25:40.208 --> 25:43.041
with the most important night
of our summer.

25:44.083 --> 25:47.833
Tonight is Sunnyvale versus Shadyside.

25:47.916 --> 25:51.583
It is red versus blue.
It is good versus evil.

25:52.416 --> 25:56.166
Tonight, we commencicate Color War!

25:56.250 --> 25:59.041
-[cheering]
-It's "commence." My god.

25:59.125 --> 26:03.166
He might be dumb,
but he's kind of shagadelic.

26:03.250 --> 26:06.375
-Oh yeah!
-He's disgusting. You're disgusting.

26:06.458 --> 26:10.541
Tonight's first event
is Capture the Flag, baby.

26:10.625 --> 26:13.125
-[cheering]
-Yeah, yeah, yeah! Now, Sunnyvalers…

26:13.708 --> 26:16.041
[whispering] We have never, ever…

26:17.083 --> 26:18.625
[shouting] …lost a Color War!

26:18.708 --> 26:20.333
[cheering, chanting] Sunnyvale!

26:20.416 --> 26:22.208
So let's not let tonight

26:22.291 --> 26:24.625
be a stain on our legacy.

26:24.708 --> 26:26.208
[chanting] Sunnyvale!

26:26.291 --> 26:27.416
[Kurt] And let's go out there

26:27.500 --> 26:31.958
like our ancestors before us

26:32.041 --> 26:36.041
and murder those Shadyside witches!

26:36.125 --> 26:38.250
-[crowd] Yeah!
-[Kurt laughs] Woo!

26:38.333 --> 26:39.916
[cheering]

26:40.000 --> 26:41.000
[cheering]

26:41.083 --> 26:42.333
Uh, hi! [giggles]

26:43.083 --> 26:45.625
Thank you, Kurt, for that neat-o speech.

26:46.375 --> 26:48.750
Now, Shadysiders,

26:49.458 --> 26:53.250
let's go out there and do our best,

26:53.333 --> 26:55.416
because even if we lose,

26:55.500 --> 26:59.250
we're still winners in our hearts.

26:59.333 --> 27:00.750
Boo!

27:00.833 --> 27:02.041
[Kurt] Boo!

27:02.125 --> 27:03.750
[booing]

27:03.833 --> 27:06.583
[chanting] Sunnyvale! Sunnyvale!

27:06.666 --> 27:09.583
["Moonage Daydream" playing]
♪ I'm an alligator ♪

27:09.666 --> 27:12.583
♪ I'm a mama-papa comin' for you ♪

27:13.291 --> 27:15.333
♪ I'm the space invader… ♪

27:15.833 --> 27:16.833
What are you doing?

27:17.958 --> 27:19.125
Art project.

27:19.208 --> 27:21.500
-I need to talk to you.
-I'm not in the mood.

27:21.583 --> 27:23.875
Earlier, you said Mary was upset.

27:23.958 --> 27:26.875
-[scoffs] Oh, so now you care!
-Ziggy, this is serious.

27:26.958 --> 27:29.583
It was serious earlier,
and you didn't give a shit.

27:32.208 --> 27:35.583
Come on, you were the last person
to see her before she snapped.

27:36.500 --> 27:38.625
What about drugs? Did you see any around?

27:39.208 --> 27:40.833
She's a nurse, so yup.

27:40.916 --> 27:43.750
-Well, did she mention anything or--
-Nope.

27:43.833 --> 27:46.958
Ziggy, I'm just… I'm trying to understand
what happened today.

27:47.041 --> 27:49.000
[Ziggy] Who cares? It's over.

27:49.083 --> 27:53.583
[Cindy] Not for Tommy. He's still
freaked out and acting weird and…

27:53.666 --> 27:57.125
It's just a big joke to everyone.
"Mary was possessed by the witch."

27:57.208 --> 27:59.083
-Maybe it was the witch.
-Ziggy…

27:59.166 --> 28:02.875
What? That doesn't fit your carefully
constructed bullshit view of the world?

28:02.958 --> 28:04.750
-Why are you being like this?
-I dunno.

28:04.833 --> 28:07.333
Maybe because Nurse Lane was
the only person who was nice to me,

28:07.416 --> 28:11.208
and now her life is over because
bad things always happen to Shadysiders.

28:11.291 --> 28:13.541
Nothing just happens.
There's always a reason.

28:13.625 --> 28:17.000
Not always a rational one.
Deep down, you feel it, don't you?

28:17.083 --> 28:21.708
Shadyside, there's something here.
It's just holding us down, cursing us.

28:21.791 --> 28:24.375
-Ziggy, that's enough.
-You're too scared to admit it.

28:24.875 --> 28:27.166
When things go bad,
you wanna explain it away.

28:27.250 --> 28:31.041
I'm sorry. I'm not going to blame
everything on some fairy tale.

28:31.125 --> 28:35.041
Life sucks sometimes. I get that.
I mean, God knows it's been hard since…

28:35.125 --> 28:36.458
Since what?

28:36.541 --> 28:38.416
See, you can't even say it!

28:38.500 --> 28:39.958
Since Dad left.

28:40.500 --> 28:41.875
Since Mom started drinking.

28:41.958 --> 28:43.791
Since we're going to lose the house.

28:43.875 --> 28:45.875
And it's not gonna magically get better.

28:46.458 --> 28:51.541
And saving up all summer to buy
a super cute polo shirt can't hide that.

28:52.625 --> 28:57.583
Trying to explain why nice old Nurse Lane
almost lost it today can't either.

28:57.666 --> 28:59.083
We're all cursed.

28:59.875 --> 29:01.250
For Mary, it was today.

29:02.208 --> 29:04.416
But someday, it'll be you.

29:04.500 --> 29:07.416
And this whole fake
bullshit life of yours,

29:07.500 --> 29:09.500
it's gonna come crashing down.

29:09.583 --> 29:11.583
That's a horrible thing to say.

29:12.375 --> 29:13.833
It's not horrible if it's true.

29:15.583 --> 29:17.958
I don't know who you are anymore, but…

29:19.625 --> 29:20.916
But you're not my sister.

29:21.875 --> 29:22.791
Then who am I?

29:23.458 --> 29:24.458
A monster.

29:25.375 --> 29:27.708
[ominous music playing]

29:29.541 --> 29:30.791
That's what they say.

29:43.916 --> 29:47.958
["Carry On Wayward Son"
playing over loudspeaker]

29:48.041 --> 29:50.833
♪ There'll be peace when you are done ♪

29:52.125 --> 29:56.083
♪ Lay your weary head to rest ♪

29:56.166 --> 29:58.416
♪ Don't you cry no more… ♪

29:59.333 --> 30:04.541
Do… do not let them anywhere near this.
Do you hear me?

30:04.625 --> 30:05.666
[all shouting] Yeah!

30:05.750 --> 30:08.333
[Kurt] I said, do you hear me?

30:08.416 --> 30:09.833
[all] Yeah!

30:11.041 --> 30:12.666
[laughter]

30:12.750 --> 30:14.458
[chanting] Shadyside! Shadyside!

30:14.541 --> 30:16.041
[whooping]

30:16.125 --> 30:17.875
[Tommy] Alright, alright, alright!

30:17.958 --> 30:21.916
Now remember, keep at least
three defenders by this all the time.

30:22.000 --> 30:23.625
Alright? And who's the jailer?

30:23.708 --> 30:27.666
OK, Jeremy, you may be
the most important player in the, uh…

30:29.166 --> 30:30.208
in the…

30:30.708 --> 30:31.708
[groans]

30:34.083 --> 30:36.500
[whispering voice echoes] Tommy…

30:36.583 --> 30:38.791
-[Cindy] Tommy!
-[chanting] Sunnyvale!

30:38.875 --> 30:40.875
-Sunnyvale!
-Are you OK?

30:40.958 --> 30:42.500
Yeah, are you OK, Mr. Slater?

30:43.458 --> 30:45.500
Yeah, I'm… I'm good. Um…

30:45.583 --> 30:47.750
Why don't you guys get started?
Plant the flag.

30:47.833 --> 30:51.500
And I'll be right behind you. OK?
Let's go, Shadyside! Come on!

30:51.583 --> 30:52.833
[chanting] Shadyside! Shadyside!

30:52.916 --> 30:54.125
Move, move, move!

30:54.208 --> 30:55.250
Oh, man.

30:56.333 --> 30:59.541
My head is throbbing.
She must have got me pretty good.

31:00.125 --> 31:03.291
-Mary's stronger than she looks.
-You need to lie down?

31:03.375 --> 31:06.125
No. No, I'm alright. I'm alright.

31:06.208 --> 31:07.666
Good. I need your help,

31:08.250 --> 31:09.958
and the key to the infirmary.

31:10.791 --> 31:14.250
[suspenseful music playing]

31:20.125 --> 31:22.375
[fire crackling]

31:30.125 --> 31:31.708
[door creaks]

31:36.000 --> 31:38.083
[Tommy] So, what exactly
are we looking for?

31:40.000 --> 31:40.916
Answers.

31:41.750 --> 31:44.083
Come on, Cindy.
It doesn't matter, alright?

31:44.166 --> 31:45.625
It matters.

31:45.708 --> 31:48.500
There's a reason Mary did what she did
and said what she said.

31:48.583 --> 31:51.666
-We're going to figure it out now.
-Come on, Cindy. Please, I…

31:51.750 --> 31:52.958
[Tommy sighs]

31:54.291 --> 31:55.291
[sighs]

32:03.000 --> 32:04.208
[chuckles]

32:04.291 --> 32:05.791
No label, half-empty.

32:06.666 --> 32:08.500
Like I said, she was on drugs.

32:09.791 --> 32:12.416
Get these to the cops,
then they'll tell us what they…

32:13.875 --> 32:14.916
What is that?

32:15.416 --> 32:17.708
"A deal was made with the Devil."

32:18.875 --> 32:21.041
"Sarah Fier cut off her wicked hand

32:21.125 --> 32:24.791
on Satan's stone
in exchange for eternal life,

32:25.500 --> 32:28.500
scarring the soil beneath
with the witch's mark,

32:29.458 --> 32:31.416
bringing Darkness upon the land."

32:33.333 --> 32:34.708
[glass breaks]

32:37.208 --> 32:38.416
Did you hear that?

32:40.916 --> 32:43.208
[menacing music playing]

32:46.291 --> 32:49.583
[floorboards creaking]

32:49.666 --> 32:50.666
[Tommy] Hello?

32:52.625 --> 32:54.291
Hello, is somebody in there?

32:57.375 --> 32:58.916
-Argh!
-Jeez!

32:59.000 --> 33:01.333
-[Alice laughing]
-Come on. That's not funny.

33:02.166 --> 33:04.791
Alice? What are you doing here?

33:04.875 --> 33:07.625
[scoffs] Looks like we're both here
for the same thing.

33:09.250 --> 33:11.291
Must really want me
to scrub those toilets.

33:11.375 --> 33:12.666
This isn't for you.

33:12.750 --> 33:15.833
Whoa, Berman. I didn't know
you were into that kind of thing.

33:15.916 --> 33:19.000
They're not for me.
I'm giving them to the cops.

33:19.083 --> 33:20.250
Oh yeah, the cops.

33:20.750 --> 33:22.250
Yeah, right, of course.

33:22.333 --> 33:26.541
No, what are you talking about?
What, now you're gonna snitch on Mary too?

33:27.125 --> 33:28.750
No. That's… I'm trying to--

33:28.833 --> 33:31.125
-This for the cops too?
-Give that back!

33:31.208 --> 33:32.875
[Alice laughing]

33:33.708 --> 33:36.375
[spooky voice]
"She emerged by the Meeting House,

33:36.458 --> 33:39.833
one hand severed, lost forever."

33:39.916 --> 33:41.791
"We hanged the witch,

33:41.875 --> 33:43.500
body chained and buried

33:43.583 --> 33:45.041
but without her hand,

33:45.583 --> 33:48.791
her grip on the land holds firm."

33:48.875 --> 33:50.166
Ooh! [laughing]

33:50.833 --> 33:52.500
This is Sarah Fier shit!

33:52.583 --> 33:54.708
Alice, come on.

33:54.791 --> 33:57.125
"When she is near, blood will fall

33:57.791 --> 34:02.250
and the curse will last
until body and hand unite."

34:02.333 --> 34:05.291
Alice, it's Mary's diary.
Let's put it back.

34:05.875 --> 34:07.000
It's not just a diary.

34:09.875 --> 34:10.958
It's a map.

34:11.541 --> 34:12.500
What?

34:12.583 --> 34:15.416
Crazy Nurse Lane made a crazy map.

34:19.250 --> 34:22.250
It's camp,
but looks like she drew all over it.

34:23.833 --> 34:26.208
1666 Union.

34:26.291 --> 34:28.416
-Union, that's Shadyside.
-What?

34:28.500 --> 34:31.875
The settlement before it was divided
into Shadyside and Sunnyvale.

34:31.958 --> 34:34.041
-Really?
-If you went to class…

34:34.125 --> 34:37.208
So, the camp is built in the same place
as the settlement?

34:38.541 --> 34:40.750
Whoa, look, look, look! Sarah Fier!

34:40.833 --> 34:43.916
-Do you think that's her house?
-[man] What are all the X's?

34:44.750 --> 34:46.416
There's only one way to find out.

34:48.291 --> 34:49.583
Hey! That's my bag!

34:49.666 --> 34:50.666
Arnie, flashlight.

34:51.333 --> 34:53.416
[Alice laughing]

34:53.500 --> 34:55.375
-What is this shit?
-Let me see.

34:55.458 --> 34:57.041
[kids playing, laughing]

34:57.958 --> 34:59.041
L484.

35:00.208 --> 35:03.166
-Sounds familiar. Ooh, Dex, maybe.
-Know what sounds fun?

35:04.041 --> 35:06.708
-Seeing a witch's house high on Dex.
-Oh yes, it does.

35:06.791 --> 35:10.458
Alice! Bring that back!
What are you doing?

35:10.541 --> 35:14.083
It's called fun, Cindy Berman.
You used to have it, remember?

35:14.166 --> 35:16.791
-[Alice] We're gonna find you, Sarah Fier!
-Tommy! [echoing]

35:17.625 --> 35:20.208
[whispering voice] Tommy…

35:20.291 --> 35:21.458
[Cindy] Tommy!

35:21.541 --> 35:23.541
Come on, they took everything!

35:24.250 --> 35:26.958
["Ever Fallen In Love" playing]

35:33.333 --> 35:34.666
[knocking on door]

35:34.750 --> 35:35.916
Go away, Cindy!

35:36.458 --> 35:37.875
It's me. It's Nick.

35:39.541 --> 35:40.875
Go away, Nick!

35:42.541 --> 35:43.375
Whoa.

35:45.166 --> 35:47.833
-I like what you've done with the place.
-This wasn't me.

35:47.916 --> 35:48.916
[Nick] I'm shocked.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.583
"Ziggy is a witch bitch."

35:51.666 --> 35:54.875
"Ziggy sucks cocks in Hell." Jeez.

35:56.166 --> 35:57.083
Sheila?

35:57.708 --> 35:58.625
Colonel Mustard.

36:00.541 --> 36:04.250
-Oh, looks like blood.
-Yeah. I didn't have a pig, so…

36:05.458 --> 36:06.458
Carrie. Cool.

36:08.375 --> 36:09.375
You've read Carrie?

36:09.458 --> 36:11.916
Yeah. Second favorite after Salem's Lot.

36:12.583 --> 36:13.625
[Ziggy chuckles]

36:13.708 --> 36:16.833
Still, I dunno,
paint seems a little pedestrian.

36:16.916 --> 36:18.916
Oh, I'm sorry. Do you have a better idea?

36:19.000 --> 36:20.416
Maybe.

36:20.500 --> 36:22.875
Shouldn't you be, like,
turning me in or something?

36:22.958 --> 36:26.541
Well, I should be supervising
Color War, uh…

36:27.500 --> 36:31.333
-But noticed you were MIA and--
-So you decided to stalk me.

36:32.000 --> 36:33.166
Check in on you.

36:33.750 --> 36:37.208
Clearly you don't need my assistance.
All good. Go ahead.

36:37.291 --> 36:38.375
"Carrie" on.

36:42.833 --> 36:43.875
What's your idea?

36:44.916 --> 36:46.000
[keys jingling]

36:47.583 --> 36:48.541
Science & Nature.

36:50.541 --> 36:51.625
[Cindy] Alice!

36:52.541 --> 36:53.541
Alice!

36:54.166 --> 36:57.000
Come on, it's disgusting in here!

36:57.083 --> 36:59.791
[Alice] We're close,
Berman, hang in there!

37:01.125 --> 37:03.125
This was the best idea.

37:04.125 --> 37:06.166
Yeah, but I still don't feel shit.

37:06.875 --> 37:08.708
OK, so, take more.

37:09.416 --> 37:10.416
Thank you.

37:12.083 --> 37:13.083
L484.

37:13.833 --> 37:15.458
-[Alice] Arnie!
-[Arnie] Wait up!

37:15.541 --> 37:16.541
[Cindy] Alice!

37:17.791 --> 37:19.916
I swear to God… [gasps]

37:21.625 --> 37:22.541
Shit!

37:22.625 --> 37:25.000
-Oh, it's ruined now!
-You cursed again.

37:26.291 --> 37:27.833
You want me to murder you?

37:28.583 --> 37:29.958
-Babe, you OK?
-[Tommy] Yeah.

37:30.041 --> 37:31.875
Yeah, I'm fine. [sniffs]

37:31.958 --> 37:33.083
[Alice screams]

37:33.958 --> 37:35.000
[Cindy] Alice?

37:36.500 --> 37:38.875
[suspenseful music playing]

37:47.666 --> 37:48.583
Watch your step.

37:51.083 --> 37:52.833
[Tommy] Is someone digging a grave?

37:54.250 --> 37:55.375
[Alice] Graves.

38:00.291 --> 38:01.375
Mary.

38:02.666 --> 38:03.875
Hey, where's the, uh…

38:05.791 --> 38:07.500
The X's, look. Look.

38:11.250 --> 38:13.583
Look, here. Here.

38:13.666 --> 38:15.166
She was marking where she dug.

38:18.250 --> 38:19.791
[Alice] "But without her hand,

38:19.875 --> 38:22.166
her grip on the land holds firm

38:22.750 --> 38:26.041
and the curse will last
until body and hand unite."

38:26.125 --> 38:28.708
Maybe Mary was looking for the hand.

38:30.958 --> 38:33.958
-To end the curse?
-That made her daughter lose her mind.

38:34.041 --> 38:35.083
Guys, come on.

38:35.166 --> 38:37.125
-[scoffs] This is silly.
-[Arnie] Yeah.

38:38.000 --> 38:39.083
I gotta piss.

38:40.625 --> 38:41.791
Hey, let me see that.

38:43.166 --> 38:44.250
You can have it,

38:44.333 --> 38:45.916
but first give me the drugs.

38:46.000 --> 38:47.541
[Arnie] L484,

38:48.416 --> 38:50.666
L484,

38:51.291 --> 38:52.291
L4…

38:53.333 --> 38:54.458
-[urine falling]
-…84.

38:54.541 --> 38:56.750
[menacing music playing]

38:56.833 --> 39:00.750
If Nurse Mary took them and went crazy,
those drugs are very dangerous.

39:00.833 --> 39:02.708
[laughing] Oh my God!

39:03.750 --> 39:05.291
What happened to you?

39:05.375 --> 39:08.291
You remember when we used to have fun?

39:09.083 --> 39:11.916
-Before you became a snitch?
-Just let it go already.

39:12.000 --> 39:13.375
That's easy for you to say.

39:13.458 --> 39:15.791
-You lying fucking Brutus.
-[Arnie] I found it!

39:18.666 --> 39:20.000
I found the witch's house.

39:20.666 --> 39:24.250
-[suspenseful music playing]
-[Alice and Arnie laughing]

39:24.333 --> 39:25.208
Dude…

39:26.375 --> 39:30.083
Was I the only one expecting, like,
I dunno, a house made out of candy?

39:30.166 --> 39:31.666
[Arnie] Maybe there's candy down here.

39:34.208 --> 39:35.625
[menacing music playing]

39:35.708 --> 39:36.958
[Alice laughing]

39:39.375 --> 39:41.041
-Whoa!
-[Alice gasps, laughs]

39:41.125 --> 39:42.875
[Alice and Arnie laughing]

39:45.500 --> 39:48.083
Hey, Sarah,
you got any candy down there? [laughing]

39:48.750 --> 39:50.333
We're high and hungry.

39:51.500 --> 39:54.041
-Sarah Fier!
-OK, we've seen enough.

39:54.125 --> 39:55.958
Alright then, go home, Berman.

39:56.500 --> 39:59.166
I didn't march all the way out here
for nothing, OK?

40:02.250 --> 40:05.166
-[Alice laughing]
-Are you crazy? Alice!

40:05.250 --> 40:06.458
Alice!

40:11.291 --> 40:13.208
[Alice] Hey, someone's been down here.

40:18.125 --> 40:19.333
Like, recently.

40:20.541 --> 40:22.208
[chuckles]

40:26.833 --> 40:29.166
[laughing] Look at all this witchy shit.

40:33.750 --> 40:35.208
It's Sarah Fier!

40:35.291 --> 40:36.750
Sarah Fier isn't real.

40:37.750 --> 40:39.708
Well, someone lit that candle.

40:45.041 --> 40:48.000
Hey, Sarah Fier, if you're in here,
say something!

40:50.166 --> 40:51.583
Maybe she's shy.

40:52.166 --> 40:53.208
[Alice chuckles]

40:55.833 --> 40:58.166
Ali… Alice! God!

40:58.916 --> 41:00.000
[Tommy exhales deeply]

41:01.958 --> 41:04.791
[dramatic music playing]

41:04.875 --> 41:06.041
Whoa!

41:08.791 --> 41:11.750
It's some kind of, like, occult thing…

41:13.458 --> 41:14.833
Like Devil worship.

41:17.250 --> 41:18.958
-[Alice] It's kinky.
-[Arnie] Oh, yeah.

41:19.041 --> 41:21.333
-[Alice laughing]
-It's the witch's mark.

41:22.208 --> 41:23.250
The what?

41:27.208 --> 41:29.375
[Cindy] "A deal was made with the Devil."

41:29.458 --> 41:32.708
"Sarah Fier cut off her wicked hand
on Satan's stone

41:32.791 --> 41:34.708
in exchange for eternal life,

41:34.791 --> 41:38.500
scarring the soil beneath
with the witch's mark,

41:39.333 --> 41:41.083
bringing Darkness upon the land."

41:41.166 --> 41:42.250
[Arnie] That's it.

41:42.750 --> 41:44.125
It's acetaminophen.

41:44.208 --> 41:46.875
-Arnie, what are you talking about?
-[Arnie] L484.

41:47.791 --> 41:51.125
It just hit me. It's fucking Tylenol.
It's nothing.

41:51.208 --> 41:52.375
Are you sure?

41:52.458 --> 41:53.458
Positive.

41:56.500 --> 41:58.500
[Arnie] Come on, Alice.
Let's get out of here.

41:58.583 --> 42:01.833
Pretty sure Joan might still have
some weed if we pay her.

42:02.333 --> 42:03.333
[sighs]

42:07.291 --> 42:08.458
[fly buzzing]

42:10.541 --> 42:12.291
[fly buzzing]

42:14.125 --> 42:15.291
[Arnie groans]

42:15.833 --> 42:17.333
[Arnie] We are out of here.

42:17.833 --> 42:19.250
Let's go, man.

42:19.333 --> 42:20.875
[indistinct whispering voice]

42:20.958 --> 42:22.416
Hey, you alright, man?

42:24.000 --> 42:25.000
Hello?

42:25.083 --> 42:26.583
[menacing music playing]

42:27.250 --> 42:28.375
[Arnie] Hello?

42:29.291 --> 42:32.666
[wind blowing]

42:32.750 --> 42:34.000
[whispering voice] Cindy.

42:36.583 --> 42:39.541
[suspenseful music playing]

42:47.791 --> 42:49.875
[whispering voice] Cindy!

42:51.583 --> 42:52.500
[gasps]

42:52.583 --> 42:54.500
-I need to show you something.
-This place…

42:55.166 --> 42:56.916
-It keeps on going.
-Now!

43:00.500 --> 43:01.500
[Alice] Cyrus Miller.

43:03.791 --> 43:05.625
Billy Barker. Ruby Lane.

43:06.125 --> 43:07.750
-Mary's daughter.
-Yeah.

43:08.250 --> 43:09.708
Isaac Milton, Harry Rooker.

43:09.791 --> 43:12.250
You don't have to go to fucking class
to know those names.

43:12.750 --> 43:14.333
-The Shadyside Killers.
-Yeah.

43:15.958 --> 43:16.958
Except one.

43:23.041 --> 43:25.500
Tommy? Alice, this isn't funny.

43:25.583 --> 43:29.916
What, you think I carved your boyfriend's
name into solid stone with my fingernails?

43:30.416 --> 43:31.916
Someone else did this.

43:37.541 --> 43:38.375
[Arnie] Tommy.

43:39.750 --> 43:40.583
[Arnie] Hello?

43:40.666 --> 43:42.208
[indistinct whispering voices]

43:44.250 --> 43:47.333
[sighs] Whatever you're on, man,
thanks for sharing.

43:48.166 --> 43:49.916
-Dick.
-[Tommy groans]

43:50.916 --> 43:53.333
[indistinct whispering voices]

43:55.166 --> 43:56.250
[Cindy] Tommy?

43:58.250 --> 44:00.500
What the hell are you doing, man? Tommy…

44:04.166 --> 44:08.208
[Cindy] Oh my God! No, no, Tommy! Stop!

44:08.291 --> 44:09.625
Tommy, stop!

44:11.375 --> 44:13.958
[both screaming]

44:14.041 --> 44:16.583
-[Cindy] Come on! Come on!
-[Alice] Fuck!

44:18.291 --> 44:20.083
[both gasping]

44:20.166 --> 44:21.291
Here.

44:21.791 --> 44:22.916
Help me.

44:23.416 --> 44:24.666
[grunting]

44:26.958 --> 44:28.750
[girls screaming]

44:28.833 --> 44:30.333
Go, go, go!

44:30.416 --> 44:32.833
[dramatic music intensifies]

44:34.208 --> 44:36.166
[Alice and Cindy grunting]

44:37.041 --> 44:39.000
[Cindy whimpering]

44:39.083 --> 44:40.708
No! No!

44:40.791 --> 44:41.875
[Cindy screaming]

44:44.625 --> 44:46.083
[Cindy screaming]

44:49.833 --> 44:51.625
[Cindy and Alice screaming]

45:00.083 --> 45:01.500
[sobbing]

45:03.250 --> 45:05.166
[distant heavy breathing]

45:08.000 --> 45:09.166
Do you hear that?

45:09.250 --> 45:12.666
[Tommy breathing heavily]

45:12.750 --> 45:14.041
He's still alive?

45:15.375 --> 45:16.750
He can't… He can't get us.

45:18.041 --> 45:19.291
[Alice breathes heavily]

45:20.958 --> 45:22.125
He can't get us.

45:22.208 --> 45:24.291
[insects chirping]

45:26.041 --> 45:27.833
[fly buzzing]

45:28.666 --> 45:30.291
[heavy footsteps]

45:31.375 --> 45:33.250
[dramatic music playing]

45:34.041 --> 45:37.125
[breathing heavily]

45:43.583 --> 45:46.125
[dramatic music intensifies]

45:50.708 --> 45:53.333
-[girl screams]
-Get in jail, Shadyside trash!

45:53.416 --> 45:55.708
-You're property of Sunnyvale now!
-[grunts]

45:56.666 --> 45:59.666
You move, you speak, you fucking die!

45:59.750 --> 46:00.750
Go!

46:01.416 --> 46:02.333
[boy] Sheila.

46:02.958 --> 46:03.791
From Will.

46:09.500 --> 46:11.000
[insects chirping]

46:11.083 --> 46:13.166
[kids playing, shouting in distance]

46:16.375 --> 46:20.291
["Don't Leave Me This Way"
playing over stereo]

46:21.083 --> 46:24.708
♪ Don't leave me this way ♪

46:26.291 --> 46:27.958
♪ I can't survive ♪

46:29.083 --> 46:30.833
♪ I can't stay alive ♪

46:31.458 --> 46:33.416
♪ Without your love… ♪

46:35.708 --> 46:38.833
Will! This is too cute.

46:38.916 --> 46:42.041
Could have done it in your bunk,
but I guess this is kind of hot.

46:43.708 --> 46:47.875
♪ I'll surely miss your tender kiss ♪

46:48.541 --> 46:51.875
♪ Don't leave me this way ♪

46:52.750 --> 46:54.208
♪ Ah, baby… ♪

46:54.291 --> 46:56.083
[screaming]

46:56.166 --> 46:58.875
♪ My heart is full of love
And desire for you ♪

46:59.541 --> 47:02.583
♪ Now come on down
And do what you gotta do…♪

47:02.666 --> 47:04.375
[screaming]

47:04.458 --> 47:07.000
Please somebody help me!

47:07.833 --> 47:09.916
Help me! Somebody help me! Please!

47:13.958 --> 47:15.375
[screaming]

47:15.458 --> 47:17.625
-[screaming echoes]
-[Ziggy and Nick laughing]

47:17.708 --> 47:20.083
-Did you hear her?
-She sounded like a frog.

47:20.166 --> 47:21.500
[mocking scream]

47:21.583 --> 47:23.416
-[Nick] What'd I tell ya?
-Fuck paint.

47:23.500 --> 47:24.583
Fuck paint.

47:24.666 --> 47:25.666
[Ziggy chuckles]

47:26.875 --> 47:27.916
Who are you?

47:28.625 --> 47:29.625
Nick Goode.

47:32.583 --> 47:33.750
Nice to meet you.

47:35.375 --> 47:36.875
[Cindy] It's some kind of cavern.

47:36.958 --> 47:39.625
I don't know. It seems to just…

47:40.666 --> 47:41.958
go on forever.

47:42.041 --> 47:43.166
[Alice] I don't care.

47:44.333 --> 47:45.333
[sighs]

47:46.958 --> 47:49.458
[Cindy] Alice, can you please just…

47:50.750 --> 47:51.916
help me?

47:52.000 --> 47:55.083
What, you're just gonna pretend
that everything's OK?

47:55.166 --> 47:57.166
[Cindy breathing heavily]

47:57.250 --> 47:58.500
Alice, I just…

47:59.458 --> 48:04.541
Tommy split Arnie's head in half.

48:05.875 --> 48:07.208
Do you realize that?

48:08.291 --> 48:10.875
-[sobbing] Please, can you just help me?
-With what?

48:11.541 --> 48:14.916
This shit weighs, like, a million pounds.
I thought you got an A in physics.

48:15.000 --> 48:16.375
We have to get out!

48:16.458 --> 48:17.625
Well, tough shit.

48:18.125 --> 48:19.541
Because we can't.

48:20.125 --> 48:22.041
We're gonna die down here.

48:23.125 --> 48:24.041
Just like Arnie.

48:25.208 --> 48:28.916
[menacing music playing]

48:29.000 --> 48:30.666
No, no. We have to get out!

48:30.750 --> 48:31.875
We have to!

48:31.958 --> 48:35.416
Those names on the wall,
they didn't stop with one murder.

48:36.416 --> 48:38.833
Seven, nine, ten, fifteen people.

48:38.916 --> 48:40.458
Those were serial killers.

48:40.541 --> 48:41.750
The campers…

48:42.666 --> 48:45.583
My… my sister, they're up there.

48:47.250 --> 48:48.541
And now, so is he.

48:49.416 --> 48:51.458
I thought you didn't believe in the witch.

48:51.541 --> 48:52.916
Yeah, I don't! I…

48:53.000 --> 48:56.208
The… There must be some… some explanation.

48:56.291 --> 48:58.958
[scoffs] Oh my God,
you are fucking unbelievable, Cindy. OK?

48:59.041 --> 49:00.416
He was possessed!

49:00.500 --> 49:03.125
-Maybe… Maybe he took a pill or--
-No!

49:03.208 --> 49:06.208
No! Cindy, no!
It wasn't the fucking Tylenol, alright?

49:06.791 --> 49:07.916
It was the witch.

49:08.500 --> 49:10.083
Alright, you saw those names.

49:10.166 --> 49:11.666
And that… that ritual,

49:12.375 --> 49:14.208
the witch is real.

49:14.875 --> 49:18.000
And she's doing some…
some fucking spell shit

49:18.083 --> 49:19.791
and possessing people.

49:19.875 --> 49:21.833
OK? Every name on that rock.

49:22.916 --> 49:24.541
And Mary knew it, alright?

49:25.041 --> 49:26.916
She knew it. And it's all right here.

49:27.000 --> 49:28.583
This isn't real!

49:30.583 --> 49:32.000
You want an explanation?

49:32.708 --> 49:34.333
Well, here it is. OK?

49:34.416 --> 49:36.916
She looked for the hand bone
to fucking stop the curse,

49:37.000 --> 49:38.958
to save Shadyside,
but she couldn't find it.

49:39.041 --> 49:40.625
Wanna know what she did find?

49:41.208 --> 49:43.916
Your boyfriend's name
in that fucking wall.

49:44.000 --> 49:44.833
[Cindy] No.

49:44.916 --> 49:47.458
-So she tried to kill him.
-Stop.

49:47.541 --> 49:49.166
Which I also would've done,

49:49.250 --> 49:52.250
if I knew there was a chance
that Tommy fucking Slater

49:52.333 --> 49:55.833
would ax my boyfriend in the fucking head!

49:55.916 --> 49:57.708
Listen! Shut up!

49:59.083 --> 50:00.208
[Alice] There we go.

50:01.541 --> 50:03.125
That's the Cindy Berman I knew.

50:05.375 --> 50:06.833
Hey, where are you going?

50:06.916 --> 50:08.375
To find another way out.

50:09.166 --> 50:10.166
Don't follow me.

50:10.750 --> 50:12.291
Don't come back here, alright?

50:13.083 --> 50:15.791
[Alice] Alright, do you hear me?
Don't come back!

50:16.291 --> 50:17.750
[breathing heavily]

50:20.541 --> 50:21.791
[whispering voice] Cindy…

50:22.291 --> 50:24.666
[gasping]

50:28.916 --> 50:30.750
You're fine, you're fine.

50:34.375 --> 50:35.541
[Alice] Boo!

50:35.625 --> 50:36.625
[Cindy gasps]

50:37.125 --> 50:40.916
Jesus, what the hell?
I told you not to follow me.

50:41.000 --> 50:42.333
Yeah, I didn't.

50:42.916 --> 50:44.416
You went in a circle.

50:45.541 --> 50:47.166
Fucking circle.

50:48.416 --> 50:51.083
[Alice laughing]

50:53.750 --> 50:55.791
[Alice laughing]

50:59.250 --> 51:01.166
[suspenseful music playing]

51:02.416 --> 51:04.916
One, two, three, four.
One, two, three, four.

51:05.000 --> 51:06.750
One, two, three, four.

51:06.833 --> 51:08.666
-What are you doing?
-Four.

51:08.750 --> 51:11.750
This symbol, it branches off here.
Four times.

51:12.291 --> 51:14.375
Three there, one there.

51:14.458 --> 51:15.916
Just like this cave.

51:16.000 --> 51:17.208
It's the same.

51:18.125 --> 51:20.541
"Sarah Fier cut off her wicked hand
on Satan's stone,

51:20.625 --> 51:23.416
scarring the soil beneath
with the witch's mark."

51:24.250 --> 51:25.791
"Scarring the soil."

51:26.500 --> 51:29.208
So, what, like, the witch
made this fucking place?

51:29.291 --> 51:31.791
Or the settlers claimed she did.
It doesn't matter.

51:31.875 --> 51:34.666
-All that matters is this symbol. It's a--
-It's a map.

51:35.375 --> 51:37.083
[menacing music intensifies]

51:37.166 --> 51:42.208
[indistinct whispering voices]

51:45.875 --> 51:49.833
Can I, uh… get you a water
or a juice box maybe?

51:49.916 --> 51:50.750
We're fine.

51:51.333 --> 51:56.958
Cool. Yeah, I just thought, you know,
since we're all in here and in jail

51:57.041 --> 51:59.750
that you might want
some refreshments, but, uh…

51:59.833 --> 52:03.250
Or we can, uh… We can… We can…
Well, we can play a game.

52:03.333 --> 52:05.041
Do you guys like, uh, Charades--

52:05.125 --> 52:06.500
Shut the fuck up, nerd.

52:08.041 --> 52:10.041
Yeah, OK. Sure. Um…

52:10.916 --> 52:11.958
[distant banging]

52:13.583 --> 52:16.041
[suspenseful music playing]

52:31.250 --> 52:32.333
[Jeremy] Sunnyvalers,

52:32.916 --> 52:35.500
these inmates are property of Shadyside.

52:36.125 --> 52:40.458
If you… If you don't leave,
I… I'll be forced to get you.

52:43.125 --> 52:46.458
[ominous music intensifies]

52:47.750 --> 52:49.291
[girl 1] Hey, nerd!

52:49.375 --> 52:51.291
[Jeremy] No. Hey, hey, hey!
That's not fair!

52:51.375 --> 52:52.875
[girl 1] Come on! Go, go!

52:52.958 --> 52:54.791
-Run, run!
-[Jeremy] No, no, no, no.

52:54.875 --> 52:56.000
[girl 2] Go, go, go!

52:56.083 --> 52:57.625
Man… [groans]

52:58.708 --> 52:59.625
[spits]

53:00.875 --> 53:01.958
[groans]

53:02.541 --> 53:06.458
[groaning]

53:07.625 --> 53:08.708
[high-pitched shrill]

53:09.375 --> 53:10.333
Tommy?

53:10.916 --> 53:12.958
[menacing music intensifies]

53:13.041 --> 53:15.000
-[Jeremy screams]
-[thud]

53:16.166 --> 53:17.583
[Tommy grunting]

53:19.458 --> 53:21.583
Alright, next question.

53:21.666 --> 53:24.250
-Uh…
-["Sweet Jane" playing over stereo]

53:24.333 --> 53:27.291
What about you and your sister?
You guys ever get along?

53:27.791 --> 53:29.958
Thought these were supposed to be
easy questions.

53:30.041 --> 53:30.916
[Nick] Says who?

53:31.000 --> 53:33.291
There are no rules to this game.

53:34.458 --> 53:35.458
God, I hate snakes.

53:35.541 --> 53:37.208
Why are you dodging my question?

53:37.791 --> 53:38.958
Why do you care?

53:39.041 --> 53:40.083
I'm curious.

53:41.666 --> 53:44.666
-I've hated her since I was a baby. Next.
-[Nick] Come on.

53:45.250 --> 53:47.875
Why are you so full of shit?

53:47.958 --> 53:49.000
[scoffs] What?

53:49.083 --> 53:50.208
Nick Goode,

53:50.750 --> 53:52.000
heir apparent,

53:52.875 --> 53:55.125
Daddy was the police chief,
the King of Sunnyvale,

53:55.208 --> 53:56.375
you're gonna be the same.

53:56.458 --> 53:58.083
Except it's all make-believe.

53:59.458 --> 54:04.166
The truth is you like Stephen King
and spiders and…

54:05.458 --> 54:07.291
the weird girl from Shadyside.

54:07.791 --> 54:08.958
Alright, first of all,

54:09.625 --> 54:12.666
Stephen King is, like, super popular.

54:13.250 --> 54:14.333
And, second,

54:15.833 --> 54:17.375
I can't like the weird girl.

54:17.458 --> 54:18.750
Why not?

54:19.541 --> 54:21.000
Because I'm a counselor.

54:21.083 --> 54:22.333
She's a camper.

54:22.416 --> 54:24.458
Last year for me. First year for you.

54:24.541 --> 54:29.833
Plus, how will I ever get to know her
when she keeps dodging my questions?

54:41.458 --> 54:44.000
There was a time
when things were good between us.

54:44.083 --> 54:47.333
When my dad was around
and my mom was happy,

54:47.416 --> 54:49.208
and my sister and me, we would, um…

54:50.416 --> 54:52.625
we'd throw toilet paper
on Mr. Corkle's tree,

54:52.708 --> 54:55.375
and then go jump in the lake
in all our clothes and…

54:57.375 --> 54:58.458
And now…

55:00.250 --> 55:02.791
Now it's just gone and everything's shit.

55:05.416 --> 55:07.541
That's what happens
when you live in Shadyside.

55:08.041 --> 55:10.083
Everything turns to shit eventually.

55:10.166 --> 55:13.416
[sentimental music playing]

55:13.500 --> 55:16.333
But I wouldn't expect
a Sunnyvaler to understand.

55:17.833 --> 55:19.458
No, maybe you're right.

55:20.125 --> 55:23.833
But, uh… being the heir apparent
isn't always easy either.

55:24.708 --> 55:25.791
Before he died,

55:26.458 --> 55:29.416
my dad loaded me up with all this,

55:29.500 --> 55:31.458
you know, "You're my legacy,

55:31.541 --> 55:34.083
the future of the family
depends on you" shit.

55:35.291 --> 55:39.916
You know, he just dropped
this huge burden in my lap and…

55:40.000 --> 55:41.875
I dunno, what if I don't want that?

55:41.958 --> 55:43.958
What if that's not who I want to be?

55:44.041 --> 55:49.541
What if I want to be the kid
who likes spiders and Stephen King and--

55:49.625 --> 55:51.625
And the weird girl from Shadyside?

55:54.458 --> 55:55.375
Yeah.

55:55.458 --> 55:57.625
[sentimental music fades out]

55:57.708 --> 55:59.291
The weird girl from Shadyside.

55:59.375 --> 56:01.958
-["Sweet Jane" continues over radio]
-But, uh…

56:02.833 --> 56:05.041
I guess there's nothing I can do about it.

56:05.541 --> 56:06.500
Why not?

56:06.583 --> 56:09.750
♪ Some people
They like to go out dancing ♪

56:09.833 --> 56:13.375
Yeah, you were right. Can we, uh…
Can we go back to the easy questions?

56:14.750 --> 56:15.791
OK.

56:18.583 --> 56:19.583
Um…

56:20.375 --> 56:21.583
How about…

56:21.666 --> 56:23.666
♪ Everything is just dirt… ♪

56:23.750 --> 56:27.833
-Would you ever kiss the weird girl?
-♪ But anyone who ever had a heart ♪

56:27.916 --> 56:32.333
♪ Oh, they wouldn't turn around
And break it ♪

56:33.041 --> 56:34.916
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

56:35.000 --> 56:37.166
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

56:37.250 --> 56:39.166
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

56:39.250 --> 56:41.166
♪ Sweet Jane ♪

56:41.250 --> 56:43.625
[girl screaming]

56:43.708 --> 56:45.416
-[crowd screaming]
-[boy] He's dead!

56:45.916 --> 56:48.208
-[boy] Jeremy's dead!
-[man] No, you guys! OK? Hey!

56:48.291 --> 56:51.541
We're done. Everyone get back.
Hey, no! Color War's done! Alright?

56:51.625 --> 56:54.083
-Get out of here! Get out!
-[Ziggy gasps]

56:54.166 --> 56:56.125
[man] Let's go! Get out! Let's go!

56:56.833 --> 57:00.625
Alright, it branches off again here.
Just stay left.

57:00.708 --> 57:02.041
[Alice gasping]

57:02.125 --> 57:05.041
I cannot believe this is working.

57:05.916 --> 57:08.708
It's taking too long.
He could be back at camp already.

57:10.958 --> 57:12.416
If you have to kill him…

57:12.916 --> 57:13.916
could you?

57:14.708 --> 57:17.916
Earlier, when Mary attacked, I just…

57:20.166 --> 57:22.125
I froze. I couldn't do anything.

57:25.875 --> 57:29.958
So, no, I… I couldn't kill anyone,
much less Tommy.

57:31.208 --> 57:33.875
Well, good news. I would happily kill him.

57:34.500 --> 57:38.708
God, even now, after everything,
you're… you're still a jerk.

57:38.791 --> 57:42.541
[Alice] OK, I'm sorry. I just…
I never got what you saw in him.

57:42.625 --> 57:45.791
And that was before
the witch possessed him.

57:46.708 --> 57:47.666
Tommy… [sighs]

57:48.708 --> 57:50.083
Tommy was sweet.

57:51.041 --> 57:52.583
He made me feel like

57:53.791 --> 57:55.916
everything was going to be OK.

57:56.708 --> 57:58.208
I loved him.

57:58.291 --> 57:59.708
I really did.

57:59.791 --> 58:01.208
[Alice] I loved Arnie too.

58:02.208 --> 58:05.083
I loved that gross, high little shit.
[inhales deeply]

58:06.458 --> 58:08.458
[deep rumbling]

58:08.541 --> 58:09.666
Do you hear that?

58:11.000 --> 58:13.000
There's this space here up ahead.

58:13.833 --> 58:16.083
All roads lead here.

58:18.791 --> 58:20.583
Is there any other way around?

58:20.666 --> 58:23.833
[rumbling continues]

58:23.916 --> 58:26.625
[flies buzzing]

58:26.708 --> 58:28.833
[breathing heavily]

58:31.791 --> 58:32.916
[Alice] What the hell?

58:33.000 --> 58:34.750
Flies? What is this stuff?

58:34.833 --> 58:36.000
It's everywhere.

58:38.958 --> 58:39.916
Cindy?

58:41.916 --> 58:43.083
What is that?

58:43.750 --> 58:45.083
[beating]

58:45.833 --> 58:48.208
-[beating]
-[flies buzzing]

58:48.875 --> 58:49.875
[beating]

58:49.958 --> 58:51.291
Let's get out of here.

58:51.833 --> 58:53.291
[beating]

58:55.250 --> 58:58.166
-[whispering voice] Alice…
-[beating]

59:00.500 --> 59:02.291
[whispering voice] Alice…

59:11.458 --> 59:12.416
[Cindy] Alice!

59:12.500 --> 59:15.041
[Alice screaming]

59:16.083 --> 59:17.208
[Cindy] Alice?

59:17.291 --> 59:19.666
[Alice yelling]

59:19.750 --> 59:21.500
[high-pitched scream]

59:21.583 --> 59:24.375
[panting]

59:25.416 --> 59:26.916
[high-pitched scream]

59:28.916 --> 59:30.166
[yelling]

59:30.250 --> 59:31.458
[screams]

59:31.541 --> 59:34.583
[ominous music intensifies]

59:35.708 --> 59:37.583
-[bone breaks]
-[screams in pain]

59:38.875 --> 59:40.750
[whimpering]

59:40.833 --> 59:42.041
[school bell ringing]

59:42.125 --> 59:45.666
Let's go! This is not part of the game!
Go, guys! Go, go!

59:45.750 --> 59:47.916
Five, seven, eight, ten,

59:48.000 --> 59:49.875
fifteen, eighteen…

59:49.958 --> 59:52.791
[kids screaming]

59:52.875 --> 59:56.541
-[Nick] Stay calm! Everything's alright!
-How many?

59:56.625 --> 59:58.916
-Twenty-three.
-That's 30 missing at least.

59:59.000 --> 1:00:01.833
-Where's Cindy, Kurt, Joan?
-I don't know. I haven't seen them.

1:00:01.916 --> 1:00:03.375
Or Tommy or anyone.

1:00:03.458 --> 1:00:06.000
-[boy] The lights are coming on!
-Maybe they're looking for us.

1:00:06.083 --> 1:00:08.500
-[Nick] It's dead.
-We have to go. We have to warn people.

1:00:08.583 --> 1:00:11.875
-I'm sure they heard the bell. Hey!
-My sister, she's still out there!

1:00:11.958 --> 1:00:14.250
The same sister you've hated
since you were a baby?

1:00:14.333 --> 1:00:16.375
Look, I'm sorry.

1:00:16.458 --> 1:00:19.125
I didn't mean it. Me and Gary will go.

1:00:19.625 --> 1:00:21.166
-What?
-Just please stay here.

1:00:21.250 --> 1:00:23.458
-I can't sit here!
-I'm not letting you get hurt!

1:00:24.791 --> 1:00:26.583
-[girl] What the hell?
-[Nick] OK?

1:00:27.208 --> 1:00:30.125
Please, let me do my job.

1:00:30.208 --> 1:00:33.250
I'm gonna find your sister.
Just stay here. OK?

1:00:33.333 --> 1:00:35.166
[indistinct chatter]

1:00:35.250 --> 1:00:38.291
-You.
-Hey, you realize that's a camper, right?

1:00:38.375 --> 1:00:41.166
Look, you make for cabin one.
I'll head to nine.

1:00:41.250 --> 1:00:44.458
-What if the killer's still out there?
-That's the whole point, Gary.

1:00:45.625 --> 1:00:49.625
Hey, everybody! Stay here! OK? OK.

1:00:49.708 --> 1:00:52.458
[ominous music playing]

1:00:52.541 --> 1:00:53.375
Hey!

1:00:54.500 --> 1:00:57.416
-Where is she, witch?
-You kill her like you killed Jeremy?

1:00:57.500 --> 1:00:59.083
-What are you talking about?
-Sheila!

1:00:59.166 --> 1:01:00.250
Where the fuck is Sheila?

1:01:02.041 --> 1:01:02.875
Shit!

1:01:04.708 --> 1:01:07.458
Nick! Nick, we forgot Sheila!

1:01:09.875 --> 1:01:10.958
Shit!

1:01:16.833 --> 1:01:17.833
Cindy!

1:01:18.333 --> 1:01:19.333
Kurt!

1:01:21.333 --> 1:01:22.250
Alice!

1:01:23.250 --> 1:01:24.208
Joan!

1:01:25.791 --> 1:01:27.000
Fuck.

1:01:27.083 --> 1:01:29.250
Where the fuck is everyone?

1:01:29.333 --> 1:01:33.041
-["Slow Ride" playing]
-[Joan moaning]

1:01:34.291 --> 1:01:36.416
Stay put, big boy.

1:01:36.500 --> 1:01:38.458
[Joan moaning]

1:01:38.541 --> 1:01:40.791
-[Joan screaming]
-[Kurt] Oh, yeah. Oh!

1:01:40.875 --> 1:01:42.541
♪ Take it easy… ♪

1:01:42.625 --> 1:01:45.125
[both moaning]

1:01:47.625 --> 1:01:48.666
[Kurt exhales deeply]

1:01:49.250 --> 1:01:52.625
You tell anyone about this,
and you're dead.

1:01:53.791 --> 1:01:55.541
-You hear me?
-Yeah.

1:01:57.666 --> 1:01:59.375
♪ Take it easy… ♪

1:01:59.458 --> 1:02:02.083
Just admit that Shadysiders do it better.

1:02:02.750 --> 1:02:04.375
[Kurt] I ain't admitting shit.

1:02:04.958 --> 1:02:06.166
He knows.

1:02:10.916 --> 1:02:12.958
♪ Move to the music… ♪

1:02:13.750 --> 1:02:15.625
[humming]

1:02:20.125 --> 1:02:21.958
[sighs] Yes.

1:02:26.166 --> 1:02:27.375
[high-pitched shrill]

1:02:30.208 --> 1:02:34.125
[Kurt] Joan, I can smell that shit
from here! Put it out!

1:02:34.208 --> 1:02:37.041
You know, you Sunnyvalers
are really missing out.

1:02:38.541 --> 1:02:40.041
This shit, like, really…

1:02:41.125 --> 1:02:43.250
opens up your mind.

1:02:43.333 --> 1:02:44.416
[Kurt] Put it out!

1:02:45.500 --> 1:02:49.000
[ominous music playing]

1:02:51.041 --> 1:02:53.958
[music continues over stereo]

1:02:57.291 --> 1:02:59.083
[ominous music playing]

1:03:11.541 --> 1:03:12.875
[door creaks]

1:03:15.166 --> 1:03:17.708
[fly buzzing]

1:03:19.583 --> 1:03:21.416
Okie dokie!

1:03:23.500 --> 1:03:24.333
Tommy!

1:03:25.458 --> 1:03:26.458
[screams]

1:03:28.083 --> 1:03:30.333
[grunting]

1:03:33.500 --> 1:03:36.458
[Alice grunting in pain]

1:03:36.541 --> 1:03:37.541
[Cindy] Alice!

1:03:37.625 --> 1:03:38.583
Jesus!

1:03:38.666 --> 1:03:40.000
[Alice whimpering]

1:03:40.083 --> 1:03:41.458
I was there, in the past.

1:03:41.541 --> 1:03:43.958
-You're OK.
-I saw the… the killers.

1:03:44.041 --> 1:03:46.250
They killed so many and you're next.

1:03:46.333 --> 1:03:47.875
You're fucking next!

1:03:47.958 --> 1:03:50.916
No, no, no, no.
That's not true. I'm right here.

1:03:51.000 --> 1:03:52.333
The witch did this.

1:03:53.166 --> 1:03:56.458
She did all of this. She put a curse
on Shadyside. Mary was right.

1:03:56.541 --> 1:03:57.500
I know.

1:03:58.000 --> 1:04:00.208
The cave was alive, Alice.

1:04:01.791 --> 1:04:03.125
Tylenol can't do that.

1:04:03.208 --> 1:04:04.500
[giggles, screams in pain]

1:04:05.000 --> 1:04:06.375
[gasping]

1:04:08.791 --> 1:04:10.000
[Cindy] You were right.

1:04:11.791 --> 1:04:12.791
I am a snitch.

1:04:13.916 --> 1:04:16.625
The day after we stole
Mr. Evans's JVC player,

1:04:17.500 --> 1:04:19.375
Harold Hines saw me with it.

1:04:19.458 --> 1:04:21.000
Fucking Harold Hines.

1:04:21.083 --> 1:04:23.833
[pained screaming]

1:04:23.916 --> 1:04:27.500
Next thing I know,
I'm in the Principal's office,

1:04:27.583 --> 1:04:29.333
and my dad can't come in

1:04:29.416 --> 1:04:33.208
because he just ran off with some girl
not much older than I am now.

1:04:33.291 --> 1:04:38.250
And my mom, well, she was having
a few drinks at O'Connell's.

1:04:38.333 --> 1:04:39.708
And I knew then…

1:04:41.083 --> 1:04:43.250
I wasn't different
from the other Shadysiders.

1:04:44.458 --> 1:04:45.750
I was cursed.

1:04:47.333 --> 1:04:49.375
I told myself if I was perfect,

1:04:49.458 --> 1:04:51.291
if I did everything right,

1:04:51.375 --> 1:04:52.916
I could beat it.

1:04:53.666 --> 1:04:55.041
I snitched on you,

1:04:55.833 --> 1:04:57.250
I got new friends, I…

1:04:58.708 --> 1:05:00.500
started dressing like this.

1:05:05.833 --> 1:05:07.333
I dated sweet Tommy.

1:05:09.125 --> 1:05:10.708
I avoided you,

1:05:10.791 --> 1:05:12.916
but I couldn't avoid Ziggy.

1:05:16.083 --> 1:05:19.125
Because she was always there,
reminding me of the truth.

1:05:19.208 --> 1:05:21.291
That this town, this place… [sniffs]

1:05:23.166 --> 1:05:24.166
…was cursed.

1:05:26.083 --> 1:05:27.583
And so were we.

1:05:28.833 --> 1:05:29.875
Now I know.

1:05:30.625 --> 1:05:31.833
She was right…

1:05:34.750 --> 1:05:35.916
all this time.

1:05:37.583 --> 1:05:39.416
[Alice screams]

1:05:39.500 --> 1:05:41.125
[Cindy] I've been a bad sister.

1:05:42.916 --> 1:05:44.250
I've been a bad friend.

1:05:46.833 --> 1:05:47.833
I should've just…

1:05:48.708 --> 1:05:51.750
skipped class, partied, had sex, had fun.

1:05:51.833 --> 1:05:53.541
[Alice] I hate to break it to you,

1:05:54.291 --> 1:05:55.500
but the fun…

1:05:58.708 --> 1:06:00.958
it's not any more real
than your polo shirt.

1:06:01.458 --> 1:06:02.833
There's a reason I wear these.

1:06:04.708 --> 1:06:06.916
And it's not just because they're awesome.

1:06:14.625 --> 1:06:17.666
[sighs shakily] We all have our ways
to deal with Shadyside.

1:06:23.791 --> 1:06:25.458
[hesitantly] What? What is it?

1:06:25.541 --> 1:06:27.583
[breathing heavily]

1:06:27.666 --> 1:06:28.541
This.

1:06:28.625 --> 1:06:31.791
This moss, it stained my shirt.
The outhouse!

1:06:36.791 --> 1:06:39.250
This stuff is all over the outhouse.

1:06:41.583 --> 1:06:42.708
Camp.

1:06:44.833 --> 1:06:46.250
It means we're close.

1:06:47.291 --> 1:06:50.208
Everyone, listen up! The game is over!

1:06:50.791 --> 1:06:53.791
Get back to the Mess Hall
or I'll dock you a victory point!

1:06:54.833 --> 1:06:56.166
[twig breaks]

1:06:57.625 --> 1:06:59.250
Claire! Freddy! Jesus!

1:06:59.958 --> 1:07:02.500
Get to the Mess Hall! Come on! Go!

1:07:09.250 --> 1:07:10.750
Everyone, the game is over!

1:07:11.666 --> 1:07:13.291
[Nick] Get back to the Mess Hall!

1:07:13.875 --> 1:07:15.083
Was that Counselor Goode?

1:07:15.166 --> 1:07:16.791
Hey! I said no talking!

1:07:17.541 --> 1:07:20.000
-He said the game was over!
-No talking, dweeb!

1:07:20.666 --> 1:07:23.500
Just stay put.
I'll check with Counselor Goode.

1:07:23.583 --> 1:07:26.375
Hey, we need… that.

1:07:26.458 --> 1:07:27.416
[boy] Hold on.

1:07:38.000 --> 1:07:39.375
Maybe we should just leave.

1:07:42.000 --> 1:07:42.875
[boy] Shit!

1:07:49.208 --> 1:07:50.666
[ominous music playing]

1:07:51.250 --> 1:07:52.416
Counselor Tommy?

1:07:53.916 --> 1:07:56.541
[campers screaming]

1:07:56.625 --> 1:08:02.708
-[ax thudding against bodies]
-[knife drawn]

1:08:03.750 --> 1:08:05.916
[owl hooting]

1:08:07.250 --> 1:08:11.000
[breathing heavily]

1:08:12.458 --> 1:08:13.666
Oh shit!

1:08:21.708 --> 1:08:22.958
Sheila?

1:08:23.958 --> 1:08:25.500
Sheila, are you still in here?

1:08:26.208 --> 1:08:27.333
Sheila?

1:08:30.083 --> 1:08:32.125
-You bitch!
-[Ziggy screams]

1:08:32.208 --> 1:08:34.375
Sheila! Listen to me!

1:08:38.083 --> 1:08:39.250
Do you smell that?

1:08:40.083 --> 1:08:41.083
[Alice] Ugh.

1:08:41.750 --> 1:08:43.166
It smells like shit.

1:08:47.166 --> 1:08:50.125
-Is that toilet paper?
-[Cindy] It's the outhouse. It's gotta be.

1:08:54.166 --> 1:08:56.583
-[Alice] Holy shit.
-[Cindy] There it is. Look.

1:08:58.458 --> 1:08:59.458
[Sheila] Bitch!

1:09:00.250 --> 1:09:02.833
[Sheila and Ziggy grunting, screaming]

1:09:05.125 --> 1:09:07.083
I'm trying to help you! There's a killer--

1:09:08.750 --> 1:09:09.833
[Ziggy] Oh shit!

1:09:09.916 --> 1:09:12.041
-I heard shouting. What's going--?
-[Ziggy gasps]

1:09:12.750 --> 1:09:14.916
-What's going on in here?
-Is everyone OK?

1:09:15.000 --> 1:09:16.958
No! Everyone's headed back
to the Mess Hall.

1:09:17.041 --> 1:09:18.041
Where's Nick?

1:09:18.708 --> 1:09:21.666
[muffled screaming]
Help! Help! We're down here! Help!

1:09:22.250 --> 1:09:23.166
Do you hear that?

1:09:23.250 --> 1:09:26.166
[muffled shouting]

1:09:26.250 --> 1:09:27.375
[muffled] Hello?

1:09:28.333 --> 1:09:30.333
-[muffled shouting] Down here!
-Please help us!

1:09:30.416 --> 1:09:33.416
-Please, help us!
-Get us out of here!

1:09:33.500 --> 1:09:36.000
-[now louder] Hey! Hello!
-Help us!

1:09:36.083 --> 1:09:37.708
[Cindy] Will you please help us?

1:09:37.791 --> 1:09:38.750
Cindy?

1:09:38.833 --> 1:09:41.000
Ziggy? Oh my God!

1:09:41.083 --> 1:09:43.291
-What are you doing down there?
-[Cindy] It's…

1:09:43.375 --> 1:09:44.625
[Cindy panting]

1:09:44.708 --> 1:09:47.250
[Cindy] It's kind of a long story.
Are you OK?

1:09:47.333 --> 1:09:48.500
Yeah, hold on a second.

1:09:48.583 --> 1:09:50.750
Ziggy, are you OK?

1:09:50.833 --> 1:09:52.458
[muffled] Are you OK?

1:09:54.125 --> 1:09:55.208
What is going on?

1:09:55.291 --> 1:09:57.625
-My sister's in the toilet.
-What?

1:09:57.708 --> 1:09:58.875
Gary! Just help me!

1:09:59.458 --> 1:10:02.833
Come on! Go! Back to the Mess Hall,
you hear me? Let's go!

1:10:02.916 --> 1:10:05.875
[menacing music playing]

1:10:09.500 --> 1:10:11.416
If anyone's in there, the game's over!

1:10:24.333 --> 1:10:25.333
Oh God.

1:10:25.833 --> 1:10:28.458
[menacing music intensifies]

1:10:35.000 --> 1:10:36.083
Oh shit!

1:10:37.000 --> 1:10:38.958
[retching]

1:10:39.041 --> 1:10:40.125
[spits]

1:10:42.291 --> 1:10:43.666
[pants]

1:10:43.750 --> 1:10:47.250
Nick! I came out of the bathroom,
she was just dead, man! I swear to God!

1:10:49.333 --> 1:10:50.500
Jesus, man.

1:10:51.666 --> 1:10:53.083
Did you do this?

1:10:53.791 --> 1:10:56.958
-Listen, there's a fucking killer.
-What?

1:10:57.041 --> 1:10:59.958
We have to get the others out of here.
Get back to the Mess Hall.

1:11:00.041 --> 1:11:02.166
In 15 minutes, ring the bell.

1:11:02.250 --> 1:11:03.916
Ring the bell, that's the signal.

1:11:04.000 --> 1:11:06.625
Get them on the bus,
get them out of here. Alright?

1:11:06.708 --> 1:11:07.875
You hear me?

1:11:07.958 --> 1:11:09.625
Just go! Go, Kurt!

1:11:09.708 --> 1:11:11.958
[menacing music playing]

1:11:19.958 --> 1:11:22.875
-[Ziggy] Get on! We're pulling you up!
-[laughing] Yes!

1:11:23.666 --> 1:11:26.250
-[Alice] Dude, oh my God.
-Pull it. You first.

1:11:30.375 --> 1:11:31.666
[rope creaks]

1:11:33.125 --> 1:11:34.458
Now!

1:11:35.458 --> 1:11:39.583
[both grunting]

1:11:42.375 --> 1:11:44.458
[Alice grunting]

1:11:47.666 --> 1:11:49.250
[grunting]

1:11:56.333 --> 1:11:57.291
[Ziggy] Keep pulling!

1:11:58.083 --> 1:11:59.791
[door creaks open]

1:11:59.875 --> 1:12:01.875
Tommy! Tommy, what are you doi…

1:12:02.625 --> 1:12:04.000
[screams]

1:12:04.083 --> 1:12:06.250
[screaming]

1:12:08.833 --> 1:12:11.166
[Cindy and Alice screaming]

1:12:11.250 --> 1:12:13.375
[screaming]

1:12:16.750 --> 1:12:17.958
[panting]

1:12:20.166 --> 1:12:21.500
[Cindy] Ziggy!

1:12:21.583 --> 1:12:24.583
-[Cindy] Ziggy!
-[Alice] Get him off!

1:12:24.666 --> 1:12:27.041
-Ziggy! Ziggy!
-Get him off me!

1:12:28.000 --> 1:12:30.833
-[Alice] Get him off! Get him off!
-Ziggy!

1:12:32.875 --> 1:12:33.791
[Ziggy gasps]

1:12:33.875 --> 1:12:34.916
What are you doing?

1:12:35.000 --> 1:12:36.708
-He's here!
-Come on!

1:12:46.375 --> 1:12:49.416
-Did we lose him?
-Yeah, I think so. Are you OK? You hurt?

1:12:51.250 --> 1:12:52.916
It's not my blood. It's Gary's.

1:12:54.041 --> 1:12:58.416
-And yours?
-Um… Sean, Jesse, Rod, Stacey.

1:12:58.500 --> 1:13:01.291
Shadysiders. It's the curse.

1:13:01.375 --> 1:13:03.291
No, it's, uh, it's just some psycho.

1:13:03.375 --> 1:13:06.208
No, no, it's not some psycho. It's Tommy.

1:13:06.291 --> 1:13:09.916
My sister's perfect, virgin,
boring boyfriend Tommy.

1:13:10.000 --> 1:13:11.000
She did this.

1:13:11.625 --> 1:13:13.625
-[Nick] Cindy?
-The witch!

1:13:14.583 --> 1:13:16.000
That's not real, Ziggy.

1:13:16.083 --> 1:13:18.791
Exactly what Sunnyvaler would say.
I thought you were different.

1:13:18.875 --> 1:13:19.708
[bell ringing]

1:13:19.791 --> 1:13:21.875
They're getting on the bus. We have to go!

1:13:21.958 --> 1:13:26.083
-I can't! My sister is still out there!
-Ziggy, I've let a lot of people die.

1:13:26.166 --> 1:13:29.083
-Nick, this isn't your fault.
-Not you! I'm not letting you die.

1:13:30.083 --> 1:13:31.708
Because, uh… yeah!

1:13:31.791 --> 1:13:34.041
I do like the weirdo from Shadyside.

1:13:34.125 --> 1:13:35.791
Maybe once we get out of this,

1:13:35.875 --> 1:13:38.541
we could, uh…
we could start a book club or something.

1:13:38.625 --> 1:13:42.541
Maybe… I dunno, Stephen King's new one
is supposed to be good, I hear.

1:13:43.041 --> 1:13:45.791
I'm done with King.
Judy Blume for me from now on.

1:13:46.875 --> 1:13:49.041
Yeah, Judy Blume sounds, uh…
sounds perfect.

1:13:49.958 --> 1:13:52.291
You believe me, right? About the curse?

1:13:53.083 --> 1:13:55.375
Yeah, of course. I am different.

1:13:56.500 --> 1:13:58.875
Now, come on. We gotta get out of here.

1:13:58.958 --> 1:14:01.541
We'll call the cops.
Your sister's gonna be alright.

1:14:01.625 --> 1:14:03.416
First, we gotta get on that bus.

1:14:03.500 --> 1:14:05.208
[banging on door]

1:14:18.625 --> 1:14:22.458
-[breathing heavily]
-[fly buzzing]

1:14:29.791 --> 1:14:31.416
[exhales deeply]

1:14:36.125 --> 1:14:38.541
[snake hissing]

1:14:41.000 --> 1:14:42.541
[snake hissing]

1:14:53.750 --> 1:14:54.750
[Tommy grunts]

1:14:59.125 --> 1:15:01.666
[menacing music intensifies]

1:15:15.625 --> 1:15:18.041
[snake hissing]

1:15:21.375 --> 1:15:25.833
[menacing music crescendos]

1:15:29.625 --> 1:15:31.208
[snake hissing]

1:15:34.166 --> 1:15:35.958
-[Ziggy screams]
-Ziggy!

1:15:36.625 --> 1:15:38.250
[Ziggy screaming]

1:15:41.916 --> 1:15:43.250
[Nick grunts in pain]

1:15:43.333 --> 1:15:44.458
[Nick] Run.

1:15:44.541 --> 1:15:45.583
Aaah! Run!

1:15:47.291 --> 1:15:48.666
Run!

1:15:50.333 --> 1:15:52.750
[menacing music crescendos]

1:15:55.458 --> 1:15:57.250
Ziggy! [panting]

1:15:58.000 --> 1:15:59.291
Ziggy!

1:16:02.958 --> 1:16:04.833
We have to find another way out.

1:16:05.333 --> 1:16:06.708
What if there's not?

1:16:06.791 --> 1:16:08.500
[Alice] No, no, there's gotta be.

1:16:08.583 --> 1:16:11.250
We're at the outhouse. We're at camp.

1:16:11.833 --> 1:16:14.208
Come on, get the diary. We're too close.

1:16:17.833 --> 1:16:19.958
OK, these… these tunnels.

1:16:21.166 --> 1:16:23.125
The witch, she made them, right?

1:16:23.208 --> 1:16:24.208
Yeah?

1:16:25.041 --> 1:16:29.291
And, "She emerged by the Meeting House,

1:16:30.041 --> 1:16:31.625
one hand severed lost forever."

1:16:31.708 --> 1:16:34.500
The Meeting House, which is now…

1:16:36.541 --> 1:16:37.666
The Mess Hall.

1:16:38.500 --> 1:16:39.833
There's gotta be another way out.

1:16:40.875 --> 1:16:42.416
Oh God!

1:16:42.500 --> 1:16:43.791
Come on!

1:16:43.875 --> 1:16:45.916
-I'm just gonna slow you down.
-Alice!

1:16:46.000 --> 1:16:49.208
No, it's fine. I'll catch up.
You gotta save your sister.

1:16:49.291 --> 1:16:50.125
No…

1:16:50.208 --> 1:16:51.083
Go!

1:16:59.375 --> 1:17:02.833
Kurt! Will! Anybody!

1:17:04.291 --> 1:17:05.208
[gasps]

1:17:10.791 --> 1:17:14.250
[breathing heavily]

1:17:28.250 --> 1:17:29.541
[Alice grunts]

1:17:39.833 --> 1:17:41.125
"Blood will fall…"

1:17:48.291 --> 1:17:50.708
"When she is near, blood will fall."

1:17:51.916 --> 1:17:55.333
"Her hand laid to rest
atop Satan's stone."

1:18:02.750 --> 1:18:03.916
Satan's stone…

1:18:06.541 --> 1:18:08.208
[grunting]

1:18:10.541 --> 1:18:13.750
[grunting]

1:18:24.500 --> 1:18:26.500
[Cindy gasping]

1:18:28.125 --> 1:18:29.125
[gasps]

1:18:37.791 --> 1:18:40.208
[groaning]

1:18:41.916 --> 1:18:43.166
[chuckles]

1:18:44.458 --> 1:18:46.500
-Hello?
-[metal rattling]

1:18:46.583 --> 1:18:49.166
Can anyone hear me? Hello?

1:18:49.750 --> 1:18:52.333
[Cindy grunting]

1:18:52.416 --> 1:18:53.416
Hello?

1:18:54.500 --> 1:18:56.708
Can anyone hear me? Hello!

1:18:56.791 --> 1:18:58.750
[ominous music playing]

1:19:08.541 --> 1:19:09.666
[gasps]

1:19:13.041 --> 1:19:16.791
["Carry On Wayward Son"
playing over loudspeaker]

1:19:16.875 --> 1:19:19.083
♪ There'll be peace when you are done… ♪

1:19:19.166 --> 1:19:23.541
Hey! Hey, I'm over here! Help!

1:19:25.375 --> 1:19:28.125
♪ Don't you cry no more… ♪

1:19:39.541 --> 1:19:41.000
[screaming] Help!

1:19:46.208 --> 1:19:50.083
-[grate banging]
-[Cindy grunting]

1:20:00.125 --> 1:20:01.875
[knocking on door]

1:20:10.333 --> 1:20:12.291
[banging on grate]

1:20:18.166 --> 1:20:19.458
[Tommy grunting]

1:20:22.291 --> 1:20:26.000
♪ Lay your weary head to rest ♪

1:20:26.791 --> 1:20:29.125
♪ Don't you cry no more ♪

1:20:39.833 --> 1:20:43.333
♪ Masquerading as a man with a reason ♪

1:20:43.416 --> 1:20:44.833
-♪ My charade-- ♪
-[music stops]

1:20:44.916 --> 1:20:46.583
-[gasps]
-[floorboard creaks]

1:20:47.458 --> 1:20:48.916
[Ziggy screams]

1:20:50.833 --> 1:20:52.333
[Ziggy screams]

1:20:52.416 --> 1:20:53.416
Ziggy!

1:20:53.916 --> 1:20:54.916
Ziggy!

1:20:55.416 --> 1:20:57.208
[banging on grate]

1:20:57.291 --> 1:20:58.708
[Tommy grunts]

1:20:58.791 --> 1:20:59.666
[Ziggy] No!

1:21:00.666 --> 1:21:02.083
[Ziggy screams, choking]

1:21:05.250 --> 1:21:07.000
[choking]

1:21:08.208 --> 1:21:09.750
[Ziggy screams]

1:21:11.750 --> 1:21:14.000
[gasping]

1:21:15.041 --> 1:21:17.291
[Ziggy screaming]

1:21:17.375 --> 1:21:20.958
[Tommy grunting]

1:21:22.041 --> 1:21:24.000
[Ziggy gasping]

1:21:24.083 --> 1:21:25.416
[Ziggy screams]

1:21:27.666 --> 1:21:29.125
[ax scrapes floor]

1:21:30.208 --> 1:21:33.291
[ominous music playing]

1:21:43.625 --> 1:21:44.625
[Ziggy screams]

1:21:45.333 --> 1:21:46.416
[Tommy grunts]

1:21:47.208 --> 1:21:48.125
No!

1:21:48.208 --> 1:21:49.291
[knife thuds]

1:21:52.583 --> 1:21:54.500
-[breathing heavily]
-[fly buzzing]

1:21:54.583 --> 1:21:55.875
[gasps]

1:21:59.041 --> 1:22:01.250
Fuck… you!

1:22:01.750 --> 1:22:03.208
[Cindy grunts]

1:22:05.083 --> 1:22:07.750
[panting]

1:22:07.833 --> 1:22:08.833
You swore!

1:22:09.958 --> 1:22:11.291
It's becoming a habit.

1:22:11.958 --> 1:22:13.125
[chuckles]

1:22:14.541 --> 1:22:16.083
[both sobbing]

1:22:17.833 --> 1:22:19.125
[sobbing]

1:22:19.208 --> 1:22:20.875
You smell like shit.

1:22:20.958 --> 1:22:23.541
-Yeah, that's because I'm covered in it.
-Oh God.

1:22:25.125 --> 1:22:28.500
-Do you think it'll wash out?
-You might need to buy a new polo.

1:22:28.583 --> 1:22:29.750
[both chuckling]

1:22:31.416 --> 1:22:32.875
I'm so sorry, Ziggy.

1:22:34.125 --> 1:22:38.750
I'm… I'm sorry I wasn't here,
not just tonight, but every day.

1:22:38.833 --> 1:22:40.625
No, you were. You just--

1:22:40.708 --> 1:22:42.541
[Cindy] No, no. I haven't been here.

1:22:43.625 --> 1:22:44.708
I know that now.

1:22:45.625 --> 1:22:49.083
I know that you just needed me
to listen, to hear you.

1:22:50.416 --> 1:22:53.958
I thought if I just put my head down
and followed the rules,

1:22:54.458 --> 1:22:55.958
everything would be fine,

1:22:56.541 --> 1:22:58.583
that I'd get out of Shadyside, but…

1:22:59.875 --> 1:23:01.625
but now I know you were right.

1:23:03.625 --> 1:23:05.041
Everything is cursed.

1:23:07.083 --> 1:23:08.500
I could have been nicer.

1:23:09.458 --> 1:23:12.208
I could have been less of a… of a monster.

1:23:12.708 --> 1:23:13.708
Yeah. Well…

1:23:16.208 --> 1:23:17.416
You were my monster.

1:23:18.500 --> 1:23:21.541
And at the end of the day, Mom, Dad…

1:23:22.708 --> 1:23:24.458
Shadyside, Sunnyvale, I…

1:23:27.125 --> 1:23:29.458
I won't let anything pull us apart again.

1:23:29.541 --> 1:23:30.541
You hear me?

1:23:31.875 --> 1:23:33.958
-Loud and clear, ma'am.
-[distant banging]

1:23:35.791 --> 1:23:38.875
[distant banging]

1:23:42.208 --> 1:23:45.333
[distant footsteps]

1:23:50.958 --> 1:23:52.416
[heavy breathing]

1:23:52.500 --> 1:23:54.500
[suspenseful music playing]

1:23:58.875 --> 1:24:00.041
[Alice grunts]

1:24:00.125 --> 1:24:01.166
Hey, snitch!

1:24:01.875 --> 1:24:03.416
What took you so long?

1:24:05.791 --> 1:24:07.208
[Alice grunting]

1:24:07.291 --> 1:24:08.208
[Cindy] Come on!

1:24:08.791 --> 1:24:11.125
[Alice grunting]

1:24:11.791 --> 1:24:12.875
[Alice chuckles]

1:24:18.666 --> 1:24:19.708
You did it.

1:24:21.166 --> 1:24:22.166
We did it.

1:24:25.583 --> 1:24:28.208
OK, careful, OK?
This thing's like a million years old.

1:24:28.791 --> 1:24:30.166
I bought that a month ago.

1:24:30.250 --> 1:24:32.833
No, I'm not talking
about your stupid bag, genius.

1:24:33.625 --> 1:24:34.708
"Blood will fall."

1:24:35.708 --> 1:24:38.083
Satan's stone, OK? It was right there.

1:24:38.750 --> 1:24:41.750
All this time, buried under the moss,
and I found it.

1:24:42.500 --> 1:24:43.875
I fucking found it.

1:24:43.958 --> 1:24:45.333
Found what?

1:24:46.416 --> 1:24:47.541
Three guesses.

1:24:47.625 --> 1:24:51.000
[ominous music playing]

